他因为石油钻井耽搁了，Skeeter

177
00:11:48,374 --> 00:11:50,672
It's... It's offshore.
那是..那是在海上

178
00:11:50,835 --> 00:11:54,635
I'm starting to think this Stuart is a figment of your imagination,
我开始认为这个Stuart是你想象虚构出来的了

179
00:11:54,797 --> 00:11:56,049
so just forget it.
那就忘掉吧

180
00:11:56,758 --> 00:11:58,101
I'm just gonna go get a plate.
我去拿个盘子

181
00:11:58,259 --> 00:12:00,478
- Shh! - Sorry!
- 嘘！ - 抱歉

182
00:12:02,513 --> 00:12:04,766

183
00:12:07,435 --> 00:12:08,778
I got a job today.
我今天找到一份工作

184
00:12:10,897 --> 00:12:12,490
At The Jackson Journal.
在Jackson日报

185
00:12:14,859 --> 00:12:16,953
They'd be a fool not to hire you.
他们要不雇你的话就是傻子

186
00:12:17,111 --> 00:12:20,365
- To Skeeter and her job.
敬Skeeter和她的工作

187
00:12:20,531 --> 00:12:22,283
Last stop till marriage.
婚前的最后一站

188
00:12:22,867 --> 00:12:23,663
Oh!
哦

189
00:12:27,789 --> 00:12:29,917
- it's for the Miss Myrna column. - Hmm.
-Myrna小姐的专栏 -嗯

190
00:12:30,083 --> 00:12:32,177
Elizabeth, can I talk to Aibileen?
Elizabeth，我能和Aibileen谈谈吗？

191
00:12:32,919 --> 00:12:36,093
Just to help me with some of the letters till I get a knack for it.
帮我回复下这些信直到我能熟练应对

192
00:12:37,674 --> 00:12:39,017
My Aibileen?
我的Aibileen？

193
00:12:39,926 --> 00:12:42,349
Why can't you just get Constantine to help?
为什么不去找Constantine帮你？

194
00:12:47,558 --> 00:12:50,027
- Constantine quit us. - [all gasping]
-Constantine离开了我们

195
00:12:50,186 --> 00:12:52,689
Oh, my gosh. Skeeter, I'm so sorry.
哦，我的天. Skeeter，抱歉

196
00:12:52,855 --> 00:12:57,110
Anyway, I just, um... I don't really know how to answer these letters.
总之，我...我真不知道如何回复这些信

197
00:12:57,777 --> 00:13:01,577
Well, I mean, as long as it doesn't interfere with her work.
好的，只要别打扰到她工作

198
00:13:01,739 --> 00:13:03,582
I don't see why not.
我不明白为什么不行

199
00:13:06,452 --> 00:13:08,204

200
00:13:11,666 --> 00:13:12,792
Leefolt residence.
Leefolt家

201
00:13:12,959 --> 00:13:14,927
Hello. Is Elizabeth in?
你好，Elizabeth在吗

202
00:13:15,086 --> 00:13:17,555
She having bridge club right now. May I take a message?
她正在打桥牌，可以帮你留个言吗？

203
00:13:17,714 --> 00:13:21,594
Yes, please tell her Celia Foote called again.
好，请告诉她Celia Foote又打了一次电话

204
00:13:22,760 --> 00:13:24,478
I'll call back tomorrow.
我明天还会打来

205
00:13:24,637 --> 00:13:26,685
- Yes, ma'am. - Uh...
-是的，夫人 - 哦

206
00:13:26,848 --> 00:13:28,771
Miss?
小姐？

207
00:13:28,933 --> 00:13:33,279
I'm looking for some help at my house. Do you know any maids looking?
我家里需要点帮助，你知道上哪找女仆吗？

208
00:13:33,438 --> 00:13:34,610
No, ma'am.
不，夫人

209
00:13:34,772 --> 00:13:37,275
OK. It's Celia Foote.
好的，是Celia Foote

210
00:13:37,442 --> 00:13:41,117
Emerson-684. Bye now.
地址Emerson-684 再见

211
00:13:44,907 --> 00:13:46,909

212
00:13:47,076 --> 00:13:49,704
You scared the daylights out of me!
吓死我了！

213
00:13:50,538 --> 00:13:54,042
It is lunchtime, and I am suddenly hungry.
午饭时间到，我饿了

214
00:13:54,625 --> 00:13:57,424

215
00:13:57,587 --> 00:13:59,464
Honestly!
真坏！

216
00:13:59,630 --> 00:14:01,803

217
00:14:04,802 --> 00:14:06,145
Oh.
哦

218
00:14:06,304 --> 00:14:08,056
I'm still working on it, Aibileen.
我还在吃呢，Aibileen

219
00:14:11,642 --> 00:14:12,985
Who was that on the phone?
刚才谁打电话来？

220
00:14:13,144 --> 00:14:15,238
Miss Celia Foote called again.
Celia Foote小姐又打来一次

221
00:14:16,564 --> 00:14:18,441
I've never called her back, Hilly.
我从没回过她电话，Hilly

222
00:14:20,068 --> 00:14:22,241
She can't take a hint, can she?
她难道就真不明白其中的暗示？

223
00:14:22,403 --> 00:14:23,996
Who's Celia Foote?
谁是Celia Foote

224
00:14:24,155 --> 00:14:26,157
That tacky girl Johnny married.
Johnny娶的那个俗气女孩

225
00:14:26,324 --> 00:14:28,167
From Sugar Ditch.
来自Sugar Ditch

226
00:14:28,326 --> 00:14:29,873
It could have been you, Hilly.
新娘本该是你的，Hilly

227
00:14:30,036 --> 00:14:35,384
And live 30 minutes outside of town? No, thank you. 
离市区30分钟路程？才不要，谢谢

228
00:14:35,541 --> 00:14:40,468
Anyway, I ran into her at the beauty parlor, and she had the nerve to ask
总之，我在美容店遇到她，她居然敢问我

229
00:14:40,630 --> 00:14:42,678
if she could help with the Children's Benefit Ball.
她能否参与孩子的义卖舞会

230
00:14:42,840 --> 00:14:46,014
Aren't we taking non-members? The benefit has gotten so big.
我们不是在招收新会员吗？义卖现在这么火？

231
00:14:46,177 --> 00:14:49,272
Yes, but we're not telling her.
是，但我们不会告诉她

232
00:14:49,430 --> 00:14:51,478

233
00:14:51,974 --> 00:14:53,567
Thank you, Aibileen.
谢谢你，Aibileen

234
00:14:53,726 --> 00:14:55,899

235
00:14:59,023 --> 00:15:00,866
Hilly, I wish you'd just go use the bathroom.
Hilly，你去用一下卫生间吧

236
00:15:01,025 --> 00:15:02,527
I'm fine.
我很好

237
00:15:02,693 --> 00:15:04,445
Oh, she's just upset
哦，她只是有点烦

238
00:15:04,612 --> 00:15:07,365
because the nigra uses the guest bath and so do we.
因为黑人用宾客卫生间，而我们也是

239
00:15:10,868 --> 00:15:12,996
Aibileen, go check on Mae Mobley.
Aibileen，去看看Mae Mobley

240
00:15:13,162 --> 00:15:14,254
Yes, ma'am.
是的，夫人

241
00:15:15,456 --> 00:15:17,129
Just go use mine and Raleigh's.
用我和Raleigh的好了

242
00:15:17,291 --> 00:15:20,966
If Aibileen uses the guest bath, I'm sure she uses yours, too.
如果Aibileen用了宾客卫生间，我敢保证她也用过你的

243
00:15:21,129 --> 00:15:22,472
She does not.
她不会

244
00:15:23,381 --> 00:15:26,601
Wouldn't you rather them take their business outside?
你不会让她们在外面解决掉这些事吗？

245
00:15:28,344 --> 00:15:30,847
Have you all seen the cover of Life this week?
你们看过这周Life的封面了吗？

246
00:15:31,013 --> 00:15:32,390
Jackie's never looked more regal.
Jackie看起来真豪华

247
00:15:32,557 --> 00:15:35,356
Tell Raleigh every penny he spends on a colored's bathroom
告诉Raleigh每一分他都花在了有色人种的厕所上

248
00:15:35,518 --> 00:15:38,362
he'll get back in spades when y'all sell.
这点小钱他马上就能赚回来

249
00:15:38,521 --> 00:15:39,647

250
00:15:39,814 --> 00:15:43,910
it's just plain dangerous. They carry different diseases than we do.
太危险了，黑人携带着各种疾病

251
00:15:44,861 --> 00:15:45,862
Pass.
过

252
00:15:46,028 --> 00:15:49,157
That's why I've drafted the Home Health Sanitation Initiative.
所以我才起草了家庭健康与环境卫生的倡议

253
00:15:49,323 --> 00:15:50,620
The what?
什么？

254
00:15:50,783 --> 00:15:52,706
A disease-preventative bill
一个预防疾病的法案

255
00:15:52,869 --> 00:15:57,295
that requires every white home to have a separate bathroom for the colored help.
要求每个白人家庭提供一个单独供有色人种使用的卫生间

256
00:15:58,166 --> 00:16:00,510
It's been endorsed by the White Citizens' Council.
这法案受到了白人市民议会的支持

257
00:16:04,422 --> 00:16:07,517
Maybe we should just build you a bathroom outside, Hilly.
也许我们该为你在外面建个厕所，Hilly

258
00:16:07,675 --> 00:16:11,179
You ought not to joke about the colored situation.
你不该拿有色人种的问题来开玩笑

259
00:16:12,513 --> 00:16:15,187
I'll do whatever it takes to protect our children.
我会采取一切措施来保护我们的孩子

260
00:16:17,059 --> 00:16:18,936
Your lead, Elizabeth.
该你了，Elizabeth

261
00:16:20,021 --> 00:16:22,615

262
00:16:24,066 --> 00:16:26,034

263
00:16:30,698 --> 00:16:32,200
- Aibileen? - Yes, ma'am.
-Aibileen？ -是的，夫人

264
00:16:34,368 --> 00:16:37,292
Do you think you'd be willing to help me with those Miss Myrna letters?
你愿意帮我回复下Myrna小姐的那些信吗？

265
00:16:39,248 --> 00:16:41,876
Miss Myrna get it wrong a lot of times. Be good to get it right.
Myrna小姐经常犯错，能纠正一下很不错

266
00:16:42,043 --> 00:16:44,546

267
00:16:44,712 --> 00:16:46,134
Thank you, Aibileen.
谢谢，Aibileen

268
00:16:48,549 --> 00:16:50,142
All that talk in there today...
今天他们说的那番话...

269
00:16:51,552 --> 00:16:52,804
Hilly'S talk?
Hilly说的那些？

270
00:16:53,513 --> 00:16:55,436
I'm sorry you had to hear that.
很抱歉让你听到那些

271
00:16:55,598 --> 00:16:58,101

272
00:17:04,649 --> 00:17:06,743
Is that Preacher Green's sermon?
那是Green牧师的布道吗？

273
00:17:06,901 --> 00:17:08,995
Yes, ma'am, it is.
是的，夫人

274
00:17:09,153 --> 00:17:12,077
That reminds me so much of my maid, Constantine.
那让我想起了我家里的女仆Constantine

275
00:17:13,366 --> 00:17:16,745
I know Constantine. We're in church circle together.
我认识Constantine，我们去同一个教堂

276
00:17:17,453 --> 00:17:18,705
Have you seen her lately?
最近你有见过她吗？

277
00:17:19,997 --> 00:17:21,294
No, ma'am.
没有，夫人

278
00:17:21,457 --> 00:17:23,004
Did you know that she had quit us?
你知道她离开我们了吗？

279
00:17:23,167 --> 00:17:24,168
Quit?
离开？

280
00:17:24,335 --> 00:17:27,635
I got home from school a week ago, and my mama told me she had quit.
一周前我从学校回到家，老妈告诉我她离开了

281
00:17:27,797 --> 00:17:31,597
Back in March, she went to live with her daughter, Rachel. In Chicago.
说她三月时回芝加哥和她女儿Rachel一起生活去了

282
00:17:32,718 --> 00:17:34,766
Did you hear that? Do you have her phone number?
这事你知道吗？你知道她电话号码吗？

283
00:17:34,929 --> 00:17:37,023
There you are, Skeeter.
你在这呢，Skeeter

284
00:17:39,141 --> 00:17:41,519
Hilly wants you to put her initiative in the League newsletter.
Hilly要你把她的倡议放到俱乐部的时事通讯上

285
00:17:41,686 --> 00:17:42,687
OK.
好的

286
00:17:44,272 --> 00:17:45,865
I'll be back tomorrow, Aibileen,
我明天还会再来，Aibileen

287
00:17:46,023 --> 00:17:48,617
to get started on those Miss Myrna letters.
开始搞那些Myrna小姐的信件

288
00:17:48,776 --> 00:17:49,948
Y'all make it quick.
你们动作都快点

289
00:17:50,111 --> 00:17:52,455
Tomorrow is silver-polishing day. OK?
明天是“银装日”。好吗？

290
00:18:11,507 --> 00:18:12,884
Hi, Jameso.
嗨，Jameso.

291
00:18:13,050 --> 00:18:14,302
How you, Miss Eugenia?
你好，Eugenia小姐

292
00:18:16,387 --> 00:18:17,388
Mama?
妈妈？

293
00:18:21,392 --> 00:18:22,814
Mama.
妈妈

294
00:18:23,436 --> 00:18:25,313
Yoo-hoo.

295
00:18:35,948 --> 00:18:37,165
Mama?
妈妈？

296
00:18:37,325 --> 00:18:38,542
Back here, honey!
在这里，亲爱的！

297
00:18:40,620 --> 00:18:43,590

298
00:18:43,748 --> 00:18:45,466
Is this a little too young?
是不是太年轻了点？

299
00:18:46,250 --> 00:18:48,127
That's a little too everything.
这打扮有点太过头了

300
00:18:49,545 --> 00:18:51,218
Oh, hell. You're right.
哦，该死，你说得对

301
00:19:06,937 --> 00:19:07,984
OK.
好的

302
00:19:10,733 --> 00:19:12,076
Much better.
好多了

303
00:19:13,069 --> 00:19:15,447
Your daddy bought me this dress in '58.
你爸爸在58年给我买的这件衣服

304
00:19:16,197 --> 00:19:18,040
Mama, I want to ask you about Constantine.
妈妈，我想问你些事 关于Constantine

305
00:19:18,199 --> 00:19:20,918
Right after Ole Miss won the Sugar Bowl. Come on. You try it on.
那是在Ole Miss（大学）赢了Sugar Bowl(美国一项橄榄球赛事)之后，快，你来试下衣服

306
00:19:21,077 --> 00:19:22,203
What really happened?
到底发生了什么？

307
00:19:22,370 --> 00:19:25,294
Skeeter, your mother is sick. She wants to see you in this dress.
Skeeter，你妈妈生病了，她想看你穿这身衣服

308
00:19:25,456 --> 00:19:26,457
Unzip me.
拉开拉链

309
00:19:28,125 --> 00:19:29,172
Come on.
快点

310
00:19:31,545 --> 00:19:34,048
Did I tell you Fanny Peatrow got engaged?
我有告诉过你Peatrow订婚了吗？

311
00:19:35,132 --> 00:19:36,930
After she got that teller job,
就在她成为出纳员之后

312
00:19:37,093 --> 00:19:39,141
her mother said she was swimming in proposals.
她妈妈说她被各种求婚包围

313
00:19:39,303 --> 00:19:41,180
Good for fair Fanny Peatrow.
对Peatrow来说真好

314
00:19:41,347 --> 00:19:44,601
Eugenia, your eggs are dying. Would it kill you to go on a date?
Eugenia，你的卵子真在死亡，你出去约个会又不会死？

315
00:19:45,351 --> 00:19:49,447
Just show a little gumption. Careful now, careful.
表现出点魄力。小心点，小心

316
00:19:49,605 --> 00:19:51,903
Oh, now look at this.
哦，快瞧瞧

317
00:19:52,566 --> 00:19:55,820
This dress is just precious on you.
这衣服你穿上真漂亮

318
00:19:55,986 --> 00:19:59,991
Just take it in a little here. Little there.
就是这里要改小些，还有那里

319
00:20:02,368 --> 00:20:05,121
- Get your hair fixed. - I got a job today.
-再给你做个头发 -我今天找到份工作

320
00:20:05,287 --> 00:20:06,288
Where?
哪里？

321
00:20:06,956 --> 00:20:09,050
Writing for The Jackson Journal.
Jackson日报

322
00:20:10,376 --> 00:20:12,674
- Great.
-棒极了

323
00:20:13,421 --> 00:20:15,594
You can write my obituary!
以后我的讣告交给你了！

324
00:20:15,756 --> 00:20:19,886
"Charlotte Phelan, dead! Her daughter, still single."
“Charlotte Phelan去世！她的女儿仍然单身！”

325
00:20:20,052 --> 00:20:22,555
Mother, would it really be so bad if I never met a husband?
我没遇上一个老公就真这么糟吗，妈妈

326
00:20:22,722 --> 00:20:25,475
Skeeter! Skeeter!

327
00:20:26,517 --> 00:20:27,939
Skeeter!

328
00:20:32,648 --> 00:20:34,025
I need to ask you something.
我想问你些事情

329
00:20:38,863 --> 00:20:42,788
I read the other day about how some girls get unbalanced.
我读到过一篇文章，关于女孩们如何迷失自我

330
00:20:43,451 --> 00:20:44,794
They start thinking these...
他们会开始产生...

331
00:20:46,495 --> 00:20:48,463
...unnatural thoughts.
...一些不正常的想法

332
00:20:48,622 --> 00:20:49,965
Are you...
你还...

333
00:20:51,751 --> 00:20:56,552
Do you, uh... find men attractive?
你还...觉得男人有吸引力吗？

334
00:20:57,131 --> 00:21:01,932
Are you having unnatural thoughts about girls or women?
还是你对女孩或妇女更有兴趣？

335
00:21:03,679 --> 00:21:04,771
Oh, my God.
哦，我的天

336
00:21:04,930 --> 00:21:09,606
Because this article says there's a cure. A special root tea!
因为这篇文章说这有得治，有一个特制的茶饮

337
00:21:09,769 --> 00:21:15,151
Mother, I want to be with girls as much as you want to be with Jameso.
妈妈，我想和女孩们在一起就像你想和Jameso在一起一样

338
00:21:15,316 --> 00:21:17,489
- Eugenia! - Unless, of course, you do!
-Eugenia！-除非，你是真想！

339
00:21:17,651 --> 00:21:19,028
Oh!
哦

340
00:21:19,528 --> 00:21:20,996

341
00:21:21,155 --> 00:21:24,625
Carlton's bringing Rebecca to dinner. Try to look presentable!
Carlton会带Rebecca来吃饭。打扮下自己！

342
00:21:26,076 --> 00:21:28,795

343
00:21:28,954 --> 00:21:31,082
What the hell you know about cleaning a house, Skeeter?
关于打扫房屋你能知道什么，Skeeter?

344
00:21:31,248 --> 00:21:33,967
It's a start, Carlton.
这只是开始，Carlton.

345
00:21:34,126 --> 00:21:37,596
If you say so. I thought you wanted to write books.
既然你这样说，我以为你想自己写书

346
00:21:37,755 --> 00:21:40,850
Now, y'all leave Sister alone.
快，你们都别烦你姐姐了

347
00:21:41,008 --> 00:21:43,887
- I'm proud of you, sweetheart. - The irony of it all.
-我为你自豪，甜心  -真是讽刺啊

348
00:21:44,053 --> 00:21:46,351
Giving advice on how to keep up a home when she doesn't even...
为打扫房屋提出建议而她自己甚至都不...

349
00:21:46,514 --> 00:21:49,939
Oh, no, Pascagoula. You couldn't have known this, but I'm allergic to almonds.
哦，不，Pascagoula。你不知道吧，我对杏仁过敏

350
00:21:50,100 --> 00:21:52,819
Sorry, Miss Eugenia, I'll get you another one.
抱歉，Eugenia小姐，我重新给你拿一个

351
00:21:52,978 --> 00:21:55,527
You know, last time I had an almond, I stopped liking men.
上次我吃了个杏仁，从此我对男人不再感兴趣了

352
00:21:55,689 --> 00:21:57,236
Oh, my Lord.
哦，我的天

353
00:21:57,399 --> 00:22:01,154
Oh, no, Rebecca, it's fine. There's a special root tea for that now.
不，Rebecca，没关系，现在有一个特制茶饮专治这个。

354
00:22:01,320 --> 00:22:02,663
You have pushed it, young lady.
你别逼我，小姐

355
00:22:03,364 --> 00:22:06,493
Daddy. What happened to Constantine?
爸爸，Constantine到底怎么了？

356
00:22:06,659 --> 00:22:08,957
Uh, well...
嗯，这个...

357
00:22:09,703 --> 00:22:13,048
Constantine went to live in Chicago with her family.
Constantine回芝加哥和她的家庭一起生活

358
00:22:13,207 --> 00:22:15,710
People move on, Skeeter.
人是向前看的，Skeeter

359
00:22:15,876 --> 00:22:18,254
But I do wish that she'd stayed down here with us.
我真心希望她能留下来和我们在一起

360
00:22:23,259 --> 00:22:24,977
I don't believe you.
我不相信你

361
00:22:25,594 --> 00:22:26,595

362
00:22:26,762 --> 00:22:29,185
She would've written and told me.
她该会写信告诉我的

363
00:22:38,524 --> 00:22:40,151
Did you fire her?
你把她开除了吧？

364
00:22:40,818 --> 00:22:44,948
We were just a job to her, honey. With them, it's all about money.
宝贝，对于她来说我们只是差事。她们要的只是钱。

365
00:22:45,114 --> 00:22:48,618
You'll understand that once you've hired help of your own.
等你自己雇佣帮手的时候你会明白的

366
00:22:49,410 --> 00:22:52,254
- She raised me. - She did not!
-是她把我带大的 -她没有

367
00:22:52,413 --> 00:22:55,007
She worked here for 29 years!
她在这工作了29年！

368
00:22:55,165 --> 00:22:57,384
It was a colored thing and I put it behind me!
有色人种的事而已，我都不再想了！

369
00:22:58,127 --> 00:23:01,927
Excuse me a moment, Rebecca. My daughter has upset my cancerous ulcers.
不好意思，Rebecca。我的女儿让我癌症犯病了

370
00:23:06,844 --> 00:23:08,846

371
00:23:09,013 --> 00:23:11,232

372
00:23:48,677 --> 00:23:51,100
What you doing hiding out here, girl?
你一个人躲这干嘛呢，女孩？

373
00:23:52,765 --> 00:23:56,144
I couldn't tell Mama I didn't get asked to the dance.
我不敢告诉妈妈我没收到去舞会的邀请

374
00:23:56,310 --> 00:23:57,436
It's all right.
没关系

375
00:23:58,646 --> 00:24:02,150
Some things we just got to keep to ourselves, right?
一些事本该只有我们自己才知道，对吧？

376
00:24:03,233 --> 00:24:05,076
All the boys say I'm ugly.
那些小子都说我丑

377
00:24:06,946 --> 00:24:11,042
Mama was third runner-up in the Miss South Carolina pageant.
妈妈可是南卡罗莱纳州小姐的第三个亚军

378
00:24:11,200 --> 00:24:14,875
I wish you'd quit feeling sorry for yourself.
我希望你不再为自己感到歉意

379
00:24:15,037 --> 00:24:17,165
Now, that's ugly.
那样的你才丑

380
00:24:18,207 --> 00:24:21,757
Ugly is something that goes up inside you.
丑是在你心里生长出来的

381
00:24:21,919 --> 00:24:25,389
It's mean and hurtful, like them boys.
它刻薄又伤人，就像那些小子

382
00:24:26,715 --> 00:24:28,513
Now you're not one of them, is you?
你不是那些人，对吧？

383
00:24:29,551 --> 00:24:31,474
I didn't think so, honey.
我想你不是，亲爱的

384
00:24:36,684 --> 00:24:37,685
Every day...
每一天...

385
00:24:39,687 --> 00:24:42,486
Every day you're not dead in the ground,
你还没入土的每一天

386
00:24:42,648 --> 00:24:47,245
when you wake up in the morning, you're gonna have to make some decisions.
当你早晨醒过来时，你得做出决定

387
00:24:48,696 --> 00:24:51,119
Got to ask yourself this question:
这样问你自己：

388
00:24:51,824 --> 00:24:53,417
"Am I gonna believe
“我要不要相信

389
00:24:53,575 --> 00:24:58,251
all them bad things them fools say about me today?"
那些傻瓜说的关于我的坏话？”

390
00:25:00,207 --> 00:25:01,299
You hear me?
听到了吗？

391
00:25:01,458 --> 00:25:04,587
"Am I gonna believe all them bad things
“我要不要相信那些

392
00:25:04,753 --> 00:25:07,256
them fools say about me today'?"
傻瓜说的关于我的坏话？

393
00:25:10,134 --> 00:25:11,260
Au right?
好吗？

394
00:25:14,430 --> 00:25:18,276
As for your mama, she didn't pick her life.
至于你妈妈，她没有选择她的生活

395
00:25:19,727 --> 00:25:21,070
It picked her.
生活选择了她

396
00:25:23,856 --> 00:25:24,982
But you...
但你...

397
00:25:27,735 --> 00:25:31,410
...you're gonna do something big with yours.
...你将会用你的生活干出点大事

398
00:25:32,531 --> 00:25:34,124
You wait and see.
等着瞧吧

399
00:25:36,493 --> 00:25:39,463
Come on, go home with me till the dance over. Come on.
快，等舞会结束和我回家

400
00:25:46,628 --> 00:25:49,256

401
00:26:00,809 --> 00:26:03,779
Miss Stein, you said in your letter to write about what disturbs me,
Stein小姐，你在信里说要写下困扰自己的事

402
00:26:03,937 --> 00:26:05,234
particularly if it bothers no one else.
特别是只困扰自己的事

403
00:26:05,397 --> 00:26:06,398
Come on.
快

404
00:26:06,565 --> 00:26:08,363
And I understand that now.
我现在有点明白了

405
00:26:09,777 --> 00:26:10,949
Continue.
继续

406
00:26:12,029 --> 00:26:14,748
I'd like to write something from the point of view of the help.
我想写点东西，从女佣的角度

407
00:26:16,283 --> 00:26:18,832
These colored women raise white children,
这些照料白人小孩的有色人种

408
00:26:18,994 --> 00:26:22,294
and in 20 years, those children become the boss.
二十年后，这些小孩成为老板

409
00:26:22,456 --> 00:26:25,175
We love them and they love us,
我们爱她们，她们也爱我们

410
00:26:25,334 --> 00:26:27,632
but they can't even use the toilets in our houses.
但是她们甚至不能使用我们房里的厕所

411
00:26:27,795 --> 00:26:29,388
Don't you find that ironic, Miss Stein?
你不觉得这个很讽刺吗，Stein小姐？

412
00:26:29,546 --> 00:26:30,547
I'm listening.
我在听

413
00:26:32,091 --> 00:26:34,685
Margaret Mitchell glorified the mammy figure,
Margaret Mitchell （《乱世佳人》作者）美化了黑人保姆的形象

414
00:26:34,843 --> 00:26:36,516
- who dedicates her whole life
一个将她一声奉献给

415
00:26:36,678 --> 00:26:37,725
to a white family.
白人家庭的黑人

416
00:26:37,888 --> 00:26:41,267
But nobody ever asked Mammy how she felt about it.
但从没有人问过黑人保姆她自己感觉怎样

417
00:26:41,433 --> 00:26:44,186
So, a side to this never before heard?
所以这方面从没被人提过？

418
00:26:44,353 --> 00:26:46,276
Yes.
是的

419
00:26:46,438 --> 00:26:49,282
'Cause nobody ever really talks about it down here.
因为这边没人关心这个

420
00:26:52,111 --> 00:26:53,909
Skeeter, who are you talking to in there?
Skeeter，你在和谁说话呢？

421
00:26:54,947 --> 00:26:56,290
Go away!
走开！

422
00:26:59,910 --> 00:27:02,880
- Who was that? - My mother.
-那是谁？ -我妈妈

423
00:27:03,038 --> 00:27:04,585
Look.
看

424
00:27:04,748 --> 00:27:08,218
No maid in her right mind is ever gonna tell you the truth.
脑子正常的女仆是不会跟你谈论这个的

425
00:27:08,377 --> 00:27:11,927
That's a hell of a risk to take in a place like Jackson, Mississippi.
在密西西比Jackson这地方，谈论这个风险很大

426
00:27:12,089 --> 00:27:13,466
I already have a maid.
我已经找到一个女仆

427
00:27:15,467 --> 00:27:18,971
Really? A Negro maid has already agreed to speak with you?
真的？一个黑人女仆已经同意和你谈论这个？

428
00:27:19,805 --> 00:27:21,352
Yes, ma'am.
是的，女士

429
00:27:25,185 --> 00:27:28,189
Well... I guess I can read what you come up with.
那好...等你写好后我会看看的

430
00:27:28,355 --> 00:27:30,528
The book biz could use a little rattling.
出版界需要点不同的声音

431
00:27:30,691 --> 00:27:32,068
Thank you, Miss Stein.
谢谢你，Stein小姐

432
00:27:32,234 --> 00:27:33,986
Hey, hey, hey, all I'm saying
嘿，嘿，嘿，我的意思是

433
00:27:34,153 --> 00:27:37,123
is that I'll let you know if it's even worth pursuing.
我只会告诉你这故事是否值得深入挖掘

434
00:27:37,281 --> 00:27:40,706
And for God's sake, you're a 23-year-old educated woman.
上帝啊，你是一个23岁受过教育的妇女了

435
00:27:40,868 --> 00:27:43,041
Go get yourself an apartment.
给你自己找间公寓吧

436
00:27:47,374 --> 00:27:49,047
"Dear Miss Myrna:
“亲爱的Myrna小姐：

437
00:27:50,002 --> 00:27:52,676
When I'm chopping onions, how do I keep tears out of my eyes?"
当我在切洋葱的时候怎么才能不流泪？

438
00:27:52,838 --> 00:27:56,433
Shoot, that's easy. You tell her hold a matchstick between her teeth.
这好办.你告诉她用火柴棒撑开她的嘴巴就行

439
00:27:57,885 --> 00:27:59,432
Is it lit?
火柴要点燃嘛？

440
00:27:59,595 --> 00:28:01,222
No, ma'am.
不，女士

441
00:28:03,557 --> 00:28:06,606
Miss Leefolt said you could start right away.
Leefolt小姐说你可以马上开始动工

442
00:28:06,768 --> 00:28:11,740
Build it just like the bathroom at my house. Let's see. 
建一个就像我房里那样的卫生间. 让我看看

443
00:28:11,899 --> 00:28:15,529
- Right there. That will be nice. - Yes, ma'am.
-就在那里. 建那不错. -是的，夫人

444
00:28:15,694 --> 00:28:18,117

445
00:28:21,033 --> 00:28:23,377
My goodness, we got to run back to the car. Come on.
我的天，我们得快回车里去. 快

446
00:28:23,911 --> 00:28:25,288
Bye, Skeeter!
再见，Skeeter!

447
00:28:28,874 --> 00:28:30,467
Aibileen.

448
00:28:30,626 --> 00:28:34,256
There's something else I want to write about. I would need your help.
有些其它的事我想写，我需要你的帮助

449
00:28:37,549 --> 00:28:41,520
I want to interview you about what it's like to work as a maid.
我想采访下你，谈谈作为一个女仆的感受

450
00:28:41,678 --> 00:28:44,978
I'd like to do a book of interviews about working for white families.
我想写本书关于为白人家庭工作

451
00:28:45,807 --> 00:28:49,528
And we could show what it's like to work for, say, Elizabeth?
我们谈谈为这些人工作是什么滋味，例如，为Elizabeth？

452
00:28:49,686 --> 00:28:52,940
You know what Miss Leefolt do to me if she knew I was telling stories on her?
你明白Leefolt小姐知道我背地里谈论她后会怎么对我吗？

453
00:28:53,106 --> 00:28:56,235
I was thinking that we wouldn't have to tell her.
我在想我们不必一定得告诉她

454
00:28:56,401 --> 00:28:59,280
The other maids would have to keep it a secret, too.
其她女仆也会把这事当做秘密守护好的

455
00:28:59,446 --> 00:29:00,789
Other maids?
其她女仆？

456
00:29:02,241 --> 00:29:04,619
I was hoping to get four or five.
我希望能找四到五个

457
00:29:04,785 --> 00:29:06,332

458
00:29:06,495 --> 00:29:09,294
To show what it's really like in Jackson.
来展示Jackson这地方到底是个啥样

459
00:29:10,540 --> 00:29:12,258

460
00:29:12,417 --> 00:29:17,298
Show what y'all get paid, and the babies and the bathrooms.
展示下你们所得到的，婴儿和卫生间这些事

461
00:29:17,464 --> 00:29:18,681
The good and the bad.
好的坏的方面都写

462
00:29:18,840 --> 00:29:19,682

463
00:29:19,841 --> 00:29:22,219
I bought you this damn house. I put up with your new clothes
为你我买下这间该死的房子. 忍受你的那些新衣服

464
00:29:22,386 --> 00:29:24,935
and trips to New Orleans, but this takes the goddamn cake.
还有去新奥尔良旅行，但这太过火了

465
00:29:25,097 --> 00:29:26,314
Hilly spoke to the surgeon general,
Hilly和卫生局局长谈过

466
00:29:26,473 --> 00:29:29,192
and she also said it'll add value to our home.
她还说这会增加我们房屋的价值

467
00:29:29,351 --> 00:29:32,195
I guess Mae Mobley can go to college in that damn bathroom!
难道Mae Mobley靠那破卫生间就能去上大学

468
00:29:32,354 --> 00:29:33,606
Hilly's covering the cost and said
这些费用Hilly全包了，她还说

469
00:29:33,772 --> 00:29:35,615
you could just do William's taxes to pay her back.
你帮William缴税就算还她钱了

470
00:29:35,774 --> 00:29:37,822
We don't take orders from the Holbrooks.
我们不接受Holbrooks的指挥

471
00:29:40,737 --> 00:29:42,614
Skeeter, how you doing?
Skeeter，你好吗？

472
00:29:44,074 --> 00:29:45,075
Fine.
不错

473
00:29:46,201 --> 00:29:47,669

474
00:29:49,538 --> 00:29:51,006
Fix me a sandwich, Aibileen.
给我做个三明治，Aibileen

475
00:29:54,334 --> 00:29:56,587
Aibileen, Mae Mobley's crying her eyes out.
Aibileen，Mae Mobley哭的好厉害

476
00:30:00,799 --> 00:30:02,426
Skeeter.

477
00:30:03,051 --> 00:30:05,930
I'm sorry, but I think it's best if you leave now.
抱歉，我想你现在最好先离开

478
00:30:06,096 --> 00:30:07,894
Oh, sure, sure.
哦，当然

479
00:30:08,056 --> 00:30:11,811
And this Miss Myrna thing isn't going to work out with Aibileen.
Myrna小姐这件事Aibileen帮不上你

480
00:30:13,020 --> 00:30:14,738
I'm sorry.
抱歉

481
00:30:19,401 --> 00:30:20,573

482
00:30:20,736 --> 00:30:22,238

483
00:30:25,324 --> 00:30:28,874
You're making it hotter, flapping your arms like that, Minny.
你搞得我更热了，像那样扇，Minny

484
00:30:38,170 --> 00:30:40,764
Look how big the waves are, Minny.
看这波浪好大啊，Minny

485
00:30:40,922 --> 00:30:42,174

486
00:30:42,341 --> 00:30:45,595
Let's go to the beach. Run, get Mr. Walters!
我们去海滩吧.快，叫上Walters先生！

487
00:30:45,761 --> 00:30:47,479
He loves riding these waves!
他最爱乘波踏浪了！

488
00:30:47,637 --> 00:30:49,935
You know we went to Biloxi on our honeymoon?
你知道 我们蜜月去的Biloxi

489
00:30:50,098 --> 00:30:51,566
Yes, ma'am.
是的，夫人

490
00:30:52,476 --> 00:30:55,400
Are we in Biloxi, Minny?
我们这是在Biloxi吗，Minny?

491
00:30:56,563 --> 00:30:59,567
No, ma'am. We ain't.
不，夫人. 我们不在

492
00:31:02,944 --> 00:31:06,915
Why don't you sit down here for a spell.
你干嘛不坐一会儿呢

493
00:31:08,116 --> 00:31:12,872
And then me and you will go on down to the beach in a little while.
然后过会儿我们一起去海滩

494
00:31:13,038 --> 00:31:14,381
How about that?
怎么样？

495
00:31:24,007 --> 00:31:25,805

496
00:31:26,843 --> 00:31:28,265
Uh...
嗯...

497
00:31:29,179 --> 00:31:30,180
Miss Hilly?
Hilly小姐？

498
00:31:30,347 --> 00:31:31,940
Mm-hm?
嗯哼？

499
00:31:34,476 --> 00:31:35,773
Never mind.
没事

500
00:31:35,936 --> 00:31:38,815
You go on ahead and use the inside bath, Minny, it's all right.
去吧，用屋里的厕所，Minny，没关系

501
00:31:38,980 --> 00:31:41,904
Oh, for crying out loud, it's just a little rain.
哦，不至于吧，就这点毛毛雨

502
00:31:42,818 --> 00:31:45,617
She can go on up and get an umbrella from William's study.
她去William的书房拿把雨伞就好

503
00:31:46,279 --> 00:31:50,034
I believe she was working for me before you dragged us both here.
她是为我工作的 在你把我们带到这里之前

504
00:31:52,119 --> 00:31:53,462

505
00:31:53,620 --> 00:31:55,793
Daddy ruined you.
你被你爸教废了

506
00:31:59,251 --> 00:32:01,128
I'm just gonna get your tea.
我去帮你拿些茶

507
00:32:26,945 --> 00:32:29,039

508
00:32:30,115 --> 00:32:31,332
Minny?

509
00:32:32,701 --> 00:32:34,374
Minny, are you in there?
Minny，你在里面吗？

510
00:32:36,413 --> 00:32:37,756
Yes, ma'am.
是的，夫人

511
00:32:38,582 --> 00:32:40,835
And just what are you doing?
你在里面干什么呢？

512
00:32:44,921 --> 00:32:45,968

513
00:32:48,717 --> 00:32:50,390
Get off my toilet!
滚出我的厕所！

514
00:32:50,552 --> 00:32:52,680

515
00:32:54,097 --> 00:32:55,440

516
00:32:55,599 --> 00:32:58,193
You are fired, Minny Jackson!
你被解雇了，Minny Jackson!

517
00:33:09,988 --> 00:33:11,740
Go on!
继续吧！

518
00:33:21,249 --> 00:33:23,923
Eighteen people died in Jackson that day.
那天Jackson 18人丧生

519
00:33:25,212 --> 00:33:27,180
Ten white and eight black.
10个白人 8个黑人

520
00:33:28,131 --> 00:33:31,101

521
00:33:31,259 --> 00:33:35,639
God don't pay no mind to color once He decide to set a tornado loose.
龙卷风下上帝不分肤色 人人平等

522
00:33:35,805 --> 00:33:38,729
Aibee's here, honey.
Aibee在这，宝贝

523
00:33:38,892 --> 00:33:40,439
Aibee's here.
Aibee在这

524
00:33:51,947 --> 00:33:54,791

525
00:34:00,747 --> 00:34:02,090

526
00:34:02,249 --> 00:34:05,423
Hurry, Aibileenl Mae Mobley is up, and I'm off to the doctor!
快，Aibileen！Mae Mobley醒来了，我要去医生那！

527
00:34:10,340 --> 00:34:14,561
That's Aibee's bathroom, Mama. Hey, Aibee!
那是Aibee的厕所，妈妈. 嗨，Aibee！

528
00:34:14,719 --> 00:34:17,188
No, no, no, honey. Promise me you won't go in there, OK?
不行，宝贝. 答应我绝不去那里面，好吗？

529
00:34:17,347 --> 00:34:18,644
- Yes, ma'am.
-是的，夫人

530
00:34:19,182 --> 00:34:20,684
I'm right here, Baby Girl.
我就在这里，宝贝！

531
00:34:22,727 --> 00:34:25,105
Isn't it so nice to have your own, Aibileen?
有自己的卫生间很不错吧，Aibileen?

532
00:34:25,272 --> 00:34:26,398
Yes, ma'am.
是的，夫人

533
00:34:41,830 --> 00:34:45,425
You're my real mama, Aibee.
你才是我的妈妈，Aibee.

534
00:34:52,882 --> 00:34:55,226

535
00:35:10,942 --> 00:35:13,286
- Is that Minny? - Minny.
-是Minny吗？ -Minny

536
00:35:14,029 --> 00:35:15,872
Hey, Aibileen!
嗨,Aibileen!

537
00:35:16,573 --> 00:35:17,574
Hey, Minny!
嗨，Minny!

538
00:35:17,741 --> 00:35:19,584
Mm-hmm.
嗯哼

539
00:35:19,743 --> 00:35:20,915
Where you headed?
你去哪？

540
00:35:22,287 --> 00:35:25,336
I got some business to tend to, so y'all just mind your own.
我要去处理些私事，你们管好自己吧

541
00:35:26,499 --> 00:35:27,967
All right, then. Well, bye!
那好. 再见！

542
00:35:28,126 --> 00:35:29,924
Bye!
再见！

543
00:35:30,086 --> 00:35:32,760
Now is she mad at me 'cause I got that job at Miss Hilly's?
她因为我得到Hilly小姐那的工作而恼火吗？

544
00:35:32,922 --> 00:35:35,596
Don't worry about her. She always mad about something.
别担心她，总有事会让她恼火

545
00:35:37,636 --> 00:35:39,058
Aibileen.

546
00:35:42,641 --> 00:35:44,643
Yes, ma'am. Everything OK?
是的，女士. 一切都好？

547
00:35:44,809 --> 00:35:46,937
Yeah, I just wanted to talk to you.
是的，我只想和你谈谈

548
00:35:47,896 --> 00:35:50,149
You got some more Miss Myrna questions for me?
你还要问我那些Myrna小姐的问题?

549
00:35:50,315 --> 00:35:51,988
Oh, no, I just wanted to talk about...
不，我想谈...

550
00:35:52,150 --> 00:35:53,242

551
00:35:55,862 --> 00:35:58,285
We never finished our conversation at Elizabeth's.
在Elizabeth家的那些谈话我们还没谈完

552
00:35:58,448 --> 00:36:00,667
About that book I want to write?
关于那本我想写的书？

553
00:36:15,548 --> 00:36:18,392
I'd really like to interview you, Aibileen.
我真想采访你，Aibileen.

554
00:36:19,386 --> 00:36:20,683
I know it's scary.
我知道这有点吓人

555
00:36:25,016 --> 00:36:27,644
They set my cousin Shinelle's car on fire,
他们把我堂妹Shinelle的车给烧了

556
00:36:27,811 --> 00:36:29,859
just 'cause she went down to the voting station.
就因为她去选举站投票

557
00:36:30,021 --> 00:36:32,274
A book like this has never been written before.
这方面的书之前从没有人写过

558
00:36:32,440 --> 00:36:34,113
'Cause there's a reason.
这是有原因的

559
00:36:34,275 --> 00:36:37,119
I do this with you, I might as well burn my own house down.
我和你这样做，我的房子也会被烧掉

560
00:36:37,278 --> 00:36:38,575
I promise we'll be careful.
我保证我们会很小心

561
00:36:38,738 --> 00:36:41,207
This already ain't careful, Miss Skeeter!
我们这样说话就很不小心，Skeeter小姐！

562
00:36:46,454 --> 00:36:49,173
You not knowing that is what's scaring me the most.
你不知道到底是什么在吓我.

563
00:36:49,332 --> 00:36:51,426
Scare me more than Jim Crow.
种族隔离法都没能这样吓到我

564
00:36:54,295 --> 00:36:55,467
An right.
好吧

565
00:36:56,256 --> 00:36:57,883
Here's my phone number.
这是我的电话号码

566
00:37:01,511 --> 00:37:04,811
- My car's here. I could take you home. - No, ma'am.
-我的车在这，我可以送你回家 -不用，女士

567
00:37:16,359 --> 00:37:20,159
"No person shall require any white female
“任何人不得要求白人女性

568
00:37:20,321 --> 00:37:24,747
to nurse in wards or rooms in which Negro men are placed.
在有黑人的病房或房间哺乳

569
00:37:26,745 --> 00:37:32,093
Books shall not be interchangeable between the white and colored schools,
白人和有色人种学校间的书籍不可互换

570
00:37:33,293 --> 00:37:37,298
but shall continue to be used by the race Hrst using them.
只得由第一个使用它们的人种继续使用

571
00:37:39,632 --> 00:37:44,934
No colored barber shall serve as a barber to white women or girls.
有色人种的理发师不得给白人女性理发

572
00:37:46,890 --> 00:37:49,234
- Any person printing, publishing
任何人擅自印刷，出版或传播

573
00:37:49,392 --> 00:37:51,235
or circulating written matter
要求社会或公众

574
00:37:51,394 --> 00:37:56,651
urging for public acceptance or social equality between whites and Negroes
平等对待白人与黑人的刊物

575
00:37:56,816 --> 00:37:58,944
is subject to imprisonment. "
都将被监禁”

576
00:38:00,153 --> 00:38:01,200
Hello?
你好？

577
00:38:01,362 --> 00:38:04,536
Aibileen, I done went and did it now.
Aibileen, 现在我做到了

578
00:38:05,575 --> 00:38:07,623
I went to Miss Hilly's house this afternoon.
下午我去Hilly小姐家

579
00:38:08,036 --> 00:38:09,288
Why Minny?
为什么 Minny?

580
00:38:09,454 --> 00:38:12,754
She done told every white woman in town I'm a thief
她告诉镇里的每个白人妇女 说我是贼

581
00:38:12,916 --> 00:38:15,385
Said I stole a candelabra.
说我偷了个烛台

582
00:38:17,545 --> 00:38:19,172
But I got her back.
但我现在还给她了

583
00:38:19,339 --> 00:38:21,012
What you did?
你做了什么？

584
00:38:22,342 --> 00:38:23,685
I can't tell you.
我不能告诉你

585
00:38:25,053 --> 00:38:27,055
I ain 't telling nobody.
我不会告诉任何人

586
00:38:28,389 --> 00:38:30,858

587
00:38:31,434 --> 00:38:35,280
I done something terrible awful to that woman,
我对那女人干了很糟的事

588
00:38:35,438 --> 00:38:38,032
and now she know what I done.
现在她知道我的能耐了

589
00:38:38,191 --> 00:38:39,488
Sorry.
抱歉

590
00:38:43,780 --> 00:38:44,781
Minny.

591
00:38:44,948 --> 00:38:46,950
She got what she deserved, Aibileen.
她罪有应得，Aibileen.

592
00:38:48,284 --> 00:38:50,912
But now I ain't gonna never get no job again.
但我将再也找不到工作

593
00:38:52,872 --> 00:38:55,170
Oh, Lord, Leroy gonna kill me.
哦，上帝，Leroy会杀了我的

594
00:38:56,626 --> 00:38:57,673

595
00:38:57,836 --> 00:38:59,509

596
00:38:59,671 --> 00:39:01,218

597
00:39:01,381 --> 00:39:02,382
Leroy?

598
00:39:04,717 --> 00:39:06,469
What you done did now, Minny?
你都干了些什么，Minny?

599
00:39:06,636 --> 00:39:07,888

600
00:39:08,054 --> 00:39:10,398
- Get off that phone, woman! - Leroy, please!
-放下电话，女人！ -Leroy，拜托！

601
00:39:10,557 --> 00:39:13,106
Minny? Minny!

602
00:39:13,268 --> 00:39:15,487
Please! Please!
拜托！

603
00:39:15,645 --> 00:39:16,771
Come here!
过来！

604
00:39:25,071 --> 00:39:28,996
Please open your Bibles to Exodus.
请将圣经翻到旧约第二卷

605
00:39:29,659 --> 00:39:32,412
Chapter four, verse ten.
第四章，第十节

606
00:39:32,912 --> 00:39:37,463
God, having asked Moses to free the Israelites...
上帝，要求摩西释放以色列人

607
00:39:37,625 --> 00:39:39,093

608
00:39:39,252 --> 00:39:40,845
...Moses answered:
...摩西回应：

609
00:39:42,213 --> 00:39:46,559
"Oh, my Lord. I am not eloquent.
“哦，主，我不胜雄辩

610
00:39:47,427 --> 00:39:51,682
I am slow of speech and slow of tongue."
我语拙口笨.”

611
00:39:51,848 --> 00:39:54,067

612
00:39:54,225 --> 00:39:58,605
See, courage isn't just about being brave.
看，勇气不只是勇敢

613
00:39:58,771 --> 00:39:59,818
Amen!
阿门！

614
00:39:59,981 --> 00:40:02,200
Courage is daring to do what is right
勇气是敢于去做对的事

615
00:40:02,442 --> 00:40:05,286
in spite of the weakness of our flesh.
不惜我们凡夫肉身

616
00:40:05,445 --> 00:40:07,823
And God tells us,
上帝告诉我们

617
00:40:08,531 --> 00:40:11,284
commands us, compels us,
指挥我们，驱使我们

618
00:40:11,451 --> 00:40:13,704
-to love. Amen? - Amen.
-去爱. 阿门 -阿门

619
00:40:13,870 --> 00:40:15,372

620
00:40:16,205 --> 00:40:17,582
See, love,
看，爱

621
00:40:17,749 --> 00:40:21,379
as exemplified by our Lord Jesus Christ,
以我主耶稣基督为例

622
00:40:21,544 --> 00:40:25,390
is to be prepared to put yourself in harm's way
他时刻准备着涉身险地

623
00:40:25,548 --> 00:40:27,516
-for your fellow man.
为了你的子民

624
00:40:27,675 --> 00:40:29,973
And by your fellow man, I mean your brother,
而借由你的子民，你的兄弟

625
00:40:30,345 --> 00:40:34,976
your sister, your neighbor, your friend and your enemy.
你的姐妹，邻居，朋友和敌人

626
00:40:35,141 --> 00:40:39,146
If you can love your enemy, you already have the victory.
如果你能爱你的敌人，那你已经胜利

627
00:40:39,312 --> 00:40:41,406
Let's stand. All right.
请起立. 好的

628
00:40:42,732 --> 00:40:44,905

629
00:40:55,495 --> 00:40:58,044

630
00:41:03,002 --> 00:41:04,299
Quick. Come quick.
快. 快点

631
00:41:04,462 --> 00:41:07,716
I parked way up on State Street and caught a cab here, like you asked.
我把车停在街那头，然后打车到这，照你吩咐那样

632
00:41:07,882 --> 00:41:09,384
Got dropped two streets over?
两个街区外下的车？

633
00:41:09,550 --> 00:41:11,018
Mm-hm.
嗯

634
00:41:25,108 --> 00:41:28,453
I know now that it's against the law, what we're doing.
我明白现在我们所作所为是违法的

635
00:41:35,994 --> 00:41:37,792
I've never seen you out of uniform before.
我从没见过你不穿制服

636
00:41:39,455 --> 00:41:41,253
You look really nice.
你看起来真漂亮

637
00:41:42,375 --> 00:41:43,592
Thank you.
谢谢

638
00:42:01,894 --> 00:42:04,738
I ain't never had no white person in my house before.
我从没让白人进过家里

639
00:42:06,858 --> 00:42:08,360
Miss Skeeter...
Skeeter小姐...

640
00:42:11,112 --> 00:42:15,788
...what if you don't like what I got to say... about white people?
如果你不喜欢我将要说的话...关于白人的？

641
00:42:17,410 --> 00:42:19,128
This isn't about me.
这不关乎我

642
00:42:20,788 --> 00:42:22,381
It doesn't matter how I feel.
我的感受不重要

643
00:42:30,757 --> 00:42:33,931
You gonna have to change my name. Mine, Miss Leefolt's. Everybody.
你必须更改我的名字. 我的，Leefolt小姐的，所有人的

644
00:42:35,428 --> 00:42:37,476
Do you have other maids that are interested?
你还认识其她感兴趣的女仆吗？

645
00:42:39,390 --> 00:42:41,392
That gonna be hard.
不大可能

646
00:42:41,559 --> 00:42:43,232
What about Minny?
那Minny呢？

647
00:42:43,394 --> 00:42:44,987
Minny got her some stories, sure enough,
当然,Minny有她自己的故事

648
00:42:45,146 --> 00:42:48,992
but she ain't real keen on talking to white peoples right now.
但她现在对和白人讲话不感兴趣

649
00:42:52,153 --> 00:42:54,747
What does it feel like to raise a white child
照顾一个白人小孩是什么感觉

650
00:42:54,906 --> 00:42:57,785
when your own child's at home being looked after by somebody else?
当你自己的小孩在家被别人照顾时？

651
00:43:00,620 --> 00:43:02,167
It feel...
那感觉...

652
00:43:14,550 --> 00:43:15,767
Is that your son?
这是你儿子吗？

653
00:43:20,932 --> 00:43:22,809
Yes, ma'am.
是的，女士

654
00:43:22,975 --> 00:43:25,148
Can we move on to the next question?
跳到下一个问题吧?

655
00:43:25,311 --> 00:43:28,190
You don't have to call me ma'am.
你不必叫我女士

656
00:43:28,773 --> 00:43:30,775
Not here.
在这里不必

657
00:43:36,739 --> 00:43:37,786
Uh...
嗯...

658
00:43:37,949 --> 00:43:40,372
Do you want to talk about the bathroom?
你想谈谈关于卫生间的事吗？

659
00:43:41,202 --> 00:43:44,172
Or anything about Miss Leefolt?
或者关于Leefolt小姐的？

660
00:43:45,164 --> 00:43:49,795
How she pays you, or has she ever yelled at you in front of Mae Mobley?
她是怎么支付你的，或者她有没有当着Mae Mobley面吼过你？

661
00:43:54,215 --> 00:43:57,560
I thought I might write my stories down and read them to you.
我想我该把自己的故事写下来读给你听

662
00:43:58,261 --> 00:44:00,355
Ain't no different than writing down my prayers.
就和我写祷文一样

663
00:44:04,308 --> 00:44:05,730
OK.
好

664
00:44:07,270 --> 00:44:08,317
Sure.
当然

665
00:44:15,695 --> 00:44:18,164
I don't say my prayers out loud.
我不会把我的祷文大声念出来

666
00:44:18,322 --> 00:44:21,496
I can get my point across a lot better writing them down.
写下这些话更能表达出我的观点

667
00:44:21,659 --> 00:44:26,711
I write an hour, sometimes two, every night.
每晚我会花一小时，有时两小时来写

668
00:44:26,873 --> 00:44:31,549
And after my prayers last night, I got some stories down, too.
昨晚就在我写完祷文后，我也写了点故事

669
00:44:34,839 --> 00:44:36,136
Go ahead.
继续

670
00:44:45,766 --> 00:44:48,861
"My first white baby to ever look after
“我照顾的第一个白人小孩

671
00:44:49,020 --> 00:44:52,240
was named Alton Carrington Speers.
名叫Alton Carrington Speers

672
00:44:52,398 --> 00:44:56,448
It was 1925, and I had just turned 14.
那是在1925年，我刚满14岁

673
00:44:57,111 --> 00:45:00,160
I dropped out of school to help Mama with the bills.
我辍学来帮妈妈维持生计

674
00:45:00,323 --> 00:45:02,917
Alton's mama died of lung disease."
Alton的妈妈死于肺病.”

675
00:45:05,119 --> 00:45:06,371

676
00:45:06,537 --> 00:45:10,462
I loved that baby. And he loved me.
我爱死那小孩了.他也爱我

677
00:45:12,919 --> 00:45:16,014
That's when I learned I could make children feel proud of theyself
就在那时我发现我可以教会孩子为自己感到自豪

678
00:45:18,716 --> 00:45:22,186
Alton used to always be asking me how come I was black.
Alton过去经常问我 我怎么是黑人

679
00:45:22,345 --> 00:45:24,393
Just ate him up.
这问题折磨死他了

680
00:45:24,555 --> 00:45:28,435
And one time, I told him it was because I drank too much coffee.
一次我告诉他我是黑人因为我喝太多咖啡

681
00:45:32,688 --> 00:45:35,316
You should have seen his face.
你真该看看他的表情

682
00:45:47,703 --> 00:45:50,297
This was just so great.
这真是太好了

683
00:45:52,291 --> 00:45:55,591
I can't tell you how much I appreciate your doing this with me.
你能这样做我真是感激不尽

684
00:45:56,837 --> 00:45:58,555
What changed your mind?
是什么改变了你的主意？

685
00:46:00,258 --> 00:46:01,384
God.
上帝

686
00:46:03,552 --> 00:46:05,520
And Miss Hilly Holbrook.
还有Hilly Holbrook小姐

687
00:46:05,680 --> 00:46:07,728

688
00:46:18,734 --> 00:46:23,410
Miss Hilly, I would like to ask you and Mr. William something.
Hilly小姐，我想问你和William先生一些事

689
00:46:26,867 --> 00:46:30,917
My twin boys graduated from high school, both on the honor roll.
我的双胞胎刚高中毕业，都是优等生

690
00:46:31,580 --> 00:46:35,050
Me and my husband, we been saving for years to send them to Tougaloo.
我和丈夫存钱很多年以便送他们去Tougaloo

691
00:46:37,044 --> 00:46:40,173
We're short about $75 on one of the tuitions.
他们中的一个学费还差75美元

692
00:46:42,216 --> 00:46:47,188
Whoo! I am late. I gotta get going.
哇！我迟了.我得走了

693
00:46:50,141 --> 00:46:51,358
See you tonight, honey.
晚上见，宝贝

694
00:46:51,517 --> 00:46:52,564
OK.
好

695
00:46:52,977 --> 00:46:54,820

696
00:46:54,979 --> 00:46:56,105
Go on.
继续

697
00:46:59,608 --> 00:47:02,487
Well, now we're...
现在我们...

698
00:47:02,653 --> 00:47:05,372
...faced with having to choose
...面临抉择

699
00:47:05,531 --> 00:47:08,159
which son can go if we don't come up with the money.
到底送哪个孩子去上学 如果钱不够的话

700
00:47:09,368 --> 00:47:11,996
Would you consider giving us a Ioan?
你能借我们一些钱吗？

701
00:47:12,747 --> 00:47:17,969
I'd work every day for free till it was paid off.
每天我免费为你工作直到我偿清贷款

702
00:47:18,127 --> 00:47:22,132
That's not working for free. That's paying off a debt.
那不是免费工作. 那是为了还贷工作

703
00:47:24,633 --> 00:47:26,135
Yes, ma'am.
是的，夫人

704
00:47:30,056 --> 00:47:34,311
As a Christian, I'm doing you a favor.
作为基督徒，我帮你个忙

705
00:47:36,062 --> 00:47:40,283
See, God don't give charity to those who are well and able.
看，上帝不会给那些健全的人施舍

706
00:47:41,442 --> 00:47:45,242
You need to come up with this money on your own. OK?
你得自己想办法弄到钱.好吗？

707
00:47:47,448 --> 00:47:49,496
Yes, ma'am.
是的，夫人

708
00:47:49,658 --> 00:47:51,126
You'll thank me one day.
迟早有一天你会感谢我的

709
00:47:53,662 --> 00:47:57,007
You cooking white food, you taste it with a different spoon.
你为白人做饭时要用不同的勺子品尝

710
00:47:57,750 --> 00:47:59,878
If they see you put the tasting spoon back in the pot,
如果他们看到你把你的勺子留在罐里

711
00:48:00,044 --> 00:48:01,387
might as well throw it all out.
就会把菜全部扔掉

712
00:48:01,545 --> 00:48:02,717
Spoon, too.
勺子也是

713
00:48:02,880 --> 00:48:06,100
And you use the same cup, same fork, same plate every day.
每天你都用同一个杯子，同一把叉子，同一个盘子

714
00:48:06,258 --> 00:48:07,851
And you put it up in the cabinet.
你把它们收进橱柜

715
00:48:08,010 --> 00:48:10,729
You tell that white woman that's where you're gonna keep it from now on out.
然后告诉白人妇女你都放哪了

716
00:48:10,888 --> 00:48:12,686
Don't do it and see what happens.
你不这样做后果会很惨

717
00:48:12,848 --> 00:48:14,521
Morning, ladies.
早安，女士们

718
00:48:14,683 --> 00:48:16,356
When you're sewing white folks coffee,
你为白人煮好咖啡后

719
00:48:16,519 --> 00:48:17,816
set it down in front of them.
要放到他们身前

720
00:48:17,978 --> 00:48:20,652
Don't hand it to them, 'cause your hands can't touch.
你不能递给他们，因为你的手不能碰到杯子

721
00:48:21,440 --> 00:48:24,159
And don't hit on they children.
还有千万不能打他们的孩子

722
00:48:24,318 --> 00:48:26,867
White folks like to do they own spanking.
打屁股的事白人喜欢自己动手

723
00:48:28,155 --> 00:48:30,658
And last thing. Come here.
最后一件事. 过来

724
00:48:31,951 --> 00:48:33,168
Look at me.
看着我

725
00:48:33,327 --> 00:48:35,671
No Sass-mouthing.
不得顶嘴

726
00:48:37,790 --> 00:48:40,168
No Sass-mouthing.
不得顶嘴

727
00:48:40,334 --> 00:48:42,052
I mean it.
我是认真的

728
00:48:47,258 --> 00:48:48,601
Give your mama a kiss.
让妈妈亲一下

729
00:48:51,262 --> 00:48:55,768
Leroy had made Sugar quit school to help him with the bills.
Leroy让Sugar辍学帮他维持生计

730
00:48:59,645 --> 00:49:03,070
And every day Minny went without a job,
每天Minny却不能工作

731
00:49:03,232 --> 00:49:05,985
might have been a day Leroy took her from our world.
也许有一天Leroy会把她带离我们的世界

732
00:49:10,448 --> 00:49:12,200
Good morning, everybody.
早上好，大家

733
00:49:19,081 --> 00:49:20,378
But I knew.
但是我知道

734
00:49:20,541 --> 00:49:24,842
I knew the only white lady Miss Hilly hadn't gotten to with her lies.
我知道有一个白人妇女没听过Hilly小姐那些谎话

735
00:49:33,220 --> 00:49:34,938
Hey!
嗨！

736
00:49:35,097 --> 00:49:38,146
Come on!
快点！

737
00:49:38,309 --> 00:49:42,780
No sass-mouthing, Minny Jackson. No Sass-mouthing.
不要顶嘴，Minny Jackson，不要顶嘴

738
00:49:44,690 --> 00:49:47,318
Aibileen said you'd be on time.
Aibileen说你会准时到

739
00:49:51,572 --> 00:49:53,449
I'm Celia Rae Foote.
我叫Celia Rae Foote

740
00:49:53,616 --> 00:49:55,289
I'm Minny Jackson.
我叫Minny Jackson

741
00:49:56,911 --> 00:49:59,960
You, uh... cooking something?
你...刚在做饭吗？

742
00:50:01,165 --> 00:50:04,590
One of those upside-down cakes from a magazine.
杂志上那些乱七八糟的蛋糕

743
00:50:04,752 --> 00:50:08,507
It ain't working out too good. Come on, let's get you a cold Coca-Cola.
结果没做好，快，先给你拿个可乐.

744
00:50:11,217 --> 00:50:12,218
Come on.
快

745
00:50:14,345 --> 00:50:16,393
This here is the kitchen.
这是厨房

746
00:50:17,640 --> 00:50:19,938
What in the hell?
这都什么乱七八糟

747
00:50:23,312 --> 00:50:25,735
I guess I got some learning to do.
看来我有得学了

748
00:50:26,482 --> 00:50:29,531
You sure do.
是有得学

749
00:50:29,693 --> 00:50:32,742
Johnny's grandmama left him this house when she died.
Johnny的奶奶死后留给他这座房子

750
00:50:32,905 --> 00:50:35,909
And then Johnny's mama wouldn't let me change a thing.
Johnny的妈妈要我保持原样

751
00:50:36,075 --> 00:50:38,077
But if I had it my way,
但如果按照我的想法

752
00:50:38,244 --> 00:50:43,125
this place would be wall-to-wall white carpet with gold trim.
这里该铺满镶带金边的地毯

753
00:50:43,290 --> 00:50:45,463
None of this old stuff.
这些老古董全都扔掉

754
00:50:45,626 --> 00:50:47,924
The main house has five beds and baths,
主房有5张床和卫生间

755
00:50:48,087 --> 00:50:52,388
and then the pool house has two more beds and baths.
泳池边的房子还有2张床和卫生间

756
00:50:52,550 --> 00:50:54,723
When y'all gonna start having some children,
你们打算何时要小孩

757
00:50:54,885 --> 00:50:56,979
filling up all these empty beds?
来塞满这么些空床？

758
00:50:59,139 --> 00:51:01,767
- I'm pregnant now. - Oh.
-我怀孕了 -哦

759
00:51:01,934 --> 00:51:05,438
Gonna be eating for two. That's double the cooking.
那你要吃两人份. 做饭得要加倍 

760
00:51:06,480 --> 00:51:09,359
I know. It's an awful lotto do.
我明白，工作量很大

761
00:51:10,401 --> 00:51:13,496
Five other maids have already turned me down.
其他五个女仆都拒绝了我

762
00:51:14,488 --> 00:51:17,116
Let me at least get you some bus money.
我至少先给你些车费吧

763
00:51:17,283 --> 00:51:20,708
Now, uh... when did you hear me say I don't want to clean this house?
...你是何时听到我不接手这房子的？

764
00:51:21,954 --> 00:51:25,208
Wait. So you'll do it?
啊.那你愿意干了？

765
00:51:28,168 --> 00:51:29,215

766
00:51:29,378 --> 00:51:30,925

767
00:51:31,755 --> 00:51:33,473
Ooh. No hugging. No hugging.
哦.别抱了.别抱了

768
00:51:34,633 --> 00:51:38,979
I'm sorry. This is the first time I've hired a maid.
抱歉，这是我第一次雇到女仆

769
00:51:39,888 --> 00:51:41,435
Come on.
快

770
00:51:41,599 --> 00:51:43,818

771
00:51:47,688 --> 00:51:51,158
- You hungry? - No, ma'am. Hold on a minute.
-你饿了吗？ -不，夫人.先等等

772
00:51:51,317 --> 00:51:53,365
We gots to talk about some things first.
有一些事我们先要说清楚

773
00:51:55,529 --> 00:51:57,406
Oh.
哦

774
00:51:57,573 --> 00:51:59,200
I work Sunday through Friday.
我从周日到周五工作

775
00:51:59,366 --> 00:52:02,370
No, you can't work at all on the weekends.
不，周末你不用工作

776
00:52:02,536 --> 00:52:05,915
OK. What time you want me here?
好.那你想我几点来？

777
00:52:07,082 --> 00:52:10,928
After 9:00, and you gotta leave before 4:00.
上午九点以后 下午四点以前

778
00:52:12,087 --> 00:52:13,259
OK.
好

779
00:52:13,422 --> 00:52:15,140
Now...
现在...

780
00:52:15,299 --> 00:52:16,892
What your husband say you can pay?
你丈夫说你能付多少钱？

781
00:52:18,552 --> 00:52:20,646
Johnny doesn't know I'm bringing in help.
Johnny不知道我有雇佣帮手

782
00:52:20,804 --> 00:52:22,898
And what Mr. Johnny gonna do when he come home
那他回到家后会怎么做

783
00:52:23,057 --> 00:52:25,230
and find a colored woman in his house?
发现一个黑女人在他房里？

784
00:52:25,392 --> 00:52:28,191
It's not like I'd be fibbing.
不是我要撒谎

785
00:52:28,354 --> 00:52:30,777
I just want him to think I can do this on my own.
我只想让他以为这些都是我一个人干的

786
00:52:32,858 --> 00:52:35,236
I really need a maid.
我真的需要一个女仆

787
00:52:37,237 --> 00:52:39,615
I'll be here tomorrow morning about 9:15.
明早9:15我会到这

788
00:52:39,782 --> 00:52:41,580

789
00:52:41,742 --> 00:52:42,868
Great.
好极了

790
00:52:46,080 --> 00:52:48,549
- Miss Celia? - Hmm?
-Celia小姐？ -嗯？

791
00:52:49,124 --> 00:52:51,001
I think you done burned up your cake.
你的蛋糕好像烤焦了

792
00:52:54,088 --> 00:52:55,431
Doggone it!
该死！

793
00:52:55,589 --> 00:52:58,593

794
00:53:01,345 --> 00:53:03,848
OK let's see. What's Hrst up on the agenda?
好，看看，日程上第一项是什么？

795
00:53:04,973 --> 00:53:10,150
We are running behind on our coat drive. Hurry up and clean out those closets.
衣服募捐活动有点滞后.我们得赶紧清理一下衣橱

796
00:53:10,312 --> 00:53:15,364
But our Christmas benefit, however, is right on schedule. Mary Beth?
但是圣诞义卖就在眼前，Mary Beth?

797
00:53:16,568 --> 00:53:21,290
Well, thanks to y'all, I can announce that we already filled
感谢大家，我宣布我们的

798
00:53:21,448 --> 00:53:24,497
every raffle slot for baked goods!
杂物架已经装满食物！

799
00:53:24,660 --> 00:53:26,253

800
00:53:26,912 --> 00:53:30,416
Think we can put a dent in African children's hunger this year?
我们会很好的帮助解决非洲儿童饥饿问题

801
00:53:31,500 --> 00:53:33,594
A big dent!
绝对的！

802
00:53:36,880 --> 00:53:37,881
Now...
现在...

803
00:53:38,048 --> 00:53:40,676
...I just found out the surgeon general
...我刚收到卫生局局长的回复

804
00:53:40,843 --> 00:53:44,222
has reviewed the Home Health Sanitation Initiative that I drafted,
关于我起草的家庭健康与环境卫生的倡议

805
00:53:44,388 --> 00:53:48,393
and he passed it along to Governor Barnett!
他已经将倡议转交给州长Barnett！

806
00:53:49,143 --> 00:53:52,568
Skeeter, when can we expect to see the initiative in the newsletter?
Skeeter,我们何时能在时事通讯中看到这份倡议？

807
00:53:52,730 --> 00:53:54,403
I gave it to you a month ago.
一个月前我就交给你了

808
00:53:54,565 --> 00:53:56,488
I gave that to you myself.
我亲自交给你的

809
00:53:56,650 --> 00:53:59,620
Would you please stand, Skeeter?
你能站起来吗，Skeeter?

810
00:54:04,491 --> 00:54:06,414
I'll have it in there real soon.
我马上着手去办

811
00:54:09,413 --> 00:54:10,665
Great.
好

812
00:54:10,831 --> 00:54:12,674

813
00:54:19,006 --> 00:54:21,384
- Sorry I'm late. - Hey.
-抱歉，我迟了 -嗨

814
00:54:29,308 --> 00:54:30,309
Thanks.
谢谢

815
00:54:35,355 --> 00:54:38,575
Hilly, I really am sorry about the newsletter.
Hilly,关于时事通讯的事我很抱歉

816
00:54:38,734 --> 00:54:41,032
It's just with Mama being sick and all.
因为老妈生病的事

817
00:54:42,988 --> 00:54:44,706
Oh, it's fine.
哦，没关系

818
00:54:47,075 --> 00:54:49,419
I made you the egg and olive on rye, Miss Skeeter.
鸡蛋和橄榄加面包，Skeeter小姐

819
00:54:49,578 --> 00:54:51,956
Oh, thank you, Henry.
哦，谢谢，Henry

820
00:54:52,122 --> 00:54:53,624
You remembered.
你还记得

821
00:54:53,791 --> 00:54:55,134
You're welcome.
不客气

822
00:54:57,628 --> 00:54:59,630
Oh, Hilly, tell her. I can hardly stand it.
哦，Hilly，告诉她，我忍不住了

823
00:55:00,506 --> 00:55:03,100
He's coming.
他来了

824
00:55:03,258 --> 00:55:06,683
Oh, Skeeter, Stuart's definitely coming this time. Next Saturday week.
哦，Skeeter，Stuart这次一定会出现，就在下周六

825
00:55:06,845 --> 00:55:11,601
Well, he's canceled twice before. Don't you think maybe that's a sign?
这个，他已经爽约两次. 你不认为这是暗示什么的吗？

826
00:55:11,767 --> 00:55:14,111
Don't you dare say that.
快别这样说

827
00:55:14,269 --> 00:55:16,021
You know I'm not gonna be his type.
你知道我不是他的菜

828
00:55:16,188 --> 00:55:18,407
Damn it, Skeeter, I'm not gonna let you miss out on this
该死，Skeeter，这次我绝不会让你错过

829
00:55:18,565 --> 00:55:21,785
because your mother convinced you you're not good enough for somebody like him.
不管你妈妈让你相信你配不上他这样优秀的男人

830
00:55:25,823 --> 00:55:27,666
Saturday night.
周六晚

831
00:56:05,821 --> 00:56:08,495
Good morning.
早

832
00:56:08,657 --> 00:56:11,581
Good morning, Baby Girl.
早，宝贝

833
00:56:11,743 --> 00:56:14,041
Good morning.
早

834
00:56:26,508 --> 00:56:28,806
I reckon I'm ready to talk about Miss Leefolt now.
我想我已经准备好谈论下Leefolt小姐了

835
00:56:31,889 --> 00:56:35,063
Baby Girl still gotta wear a diaper when she sleep at night.
晚上小女孩还是穿着尿布睡觉

836
00:56:35,225 --> 00:56:37,478
And it don't get changed till I get there in the morning.
没人会去换尿布直到我上午到那

837
00:56:37,644 --> 00:56:40,488
That about ten hours she gotta sleep in her mess.
十个小时她都和她的便便睡在一起

838
00:56:41,815 --> 00:56:44,409
Now Miss Leefolt pregnant with her second baby.
现在Leefolt小姐怀了第二胎

839
00:56:45,235 --> 00:56:48,580
Lord... I pray this child turn out good.
主啊...我祈祷这孩子能长大成人

840
00:56:49,489 --> 00:56:52,288
It's a lonely road if a mama don't think their child is pretty.
这是条孤单的道路如果妈妈认为她的孩子不够漂亮

841
00:56:55,245 --> 00:56:57,088
That's very true.
深有感触

842
00:57:00,959 --> 00:57:02,927
Miss Leefolt should not be having babies.
Leefolt小姐就不该要孩子

843
00:57:07,382 --> 00:57:08,508
Write that down.
把这句话记下

844
00:57:15,641 --> 00:57:18,315
Treelore would like me doing this.
Treelore会希望我这样做的

845
00:57:18,477 --> 00:57:21,276
He always said we were gonna have a writer in the family one day.
他总说家里迟早有一天会出个作家

846
00:57:21,438 --> 00:57:23,861
I always thought it was gonna be him. Maybe it's gonna be me.
我原想那人准是他，看来也许是我

847
00:57:24,942 --> 00:57:26,910
Aibileen, Aibileen.

848
00:57:27,069 --> 00:57:29,868
They done set a bomb off in Medgar Evers' carport.
他们在Medgar Evers车库里引爆了炸弹

849
00:57:38,372 --> 00:57:42,172
Yule Mae told me what y'all was up to. I didn't want to believe it.
Yule Mae告诉我你正在做的事，我简直不敢相信

850
00:57:44,962 --> 00:57:48,011
And just what makes you think colored people need your help?
是什么让你以为有色人种需要你的帮助？

851
00:57:49,132 --> 00:57:50,725
- Why do you care? - Minny.
-你为什么会关心？ -Minny

852
00:57:50,884 --> 00:57:52,682
Maybe you just want to get Aibileen in trouble.
也许你只想让Aibileen陷入麻烦吧

853
00:57:52,844 --> 00:57:54,437
No.
不是

854
00:57:54,596 --> 00:57:56,974
I want to show her perspective.
我想展示她的看法

855
00:57:57,140 --> 00:58:00,815
So people might understand what it's like from your side.
这样人们也许就会明白你们的感受

856
00:58:00,978 --> 00:58:03,652
Well, it's a real Fourth of July picnic.
是啊，这就是我们的梦想

857
00:58:04,231 --> 00:58:07,485
It's what we dream of doing all weekend long.
我们周末就梦想着这样干

858
00:58:07,651 --> 00:58:10,404
Get back into they house, polish the silver.
回到他们家，擦亮银器

859
00:58:10,570 --> 00:58:15,167
And we just love not making minimum wage or getting Social Security.
能拿到不是最低的工资和社保 我们真是幸运

860
00:58:17,119 --> 00:58:20,043
And how we love they children when they little.
孩子小的时候我们真好喜欢

861
00:58:20,872 --> 00:58:24,001
And then they turn out just like they mamas.
结果孩子长大后就和妈妈一个样

862
00:58:24,167 --> 00:58:25,214
I know.
我知道

863
00:58:27,254 --> 00:58:28,756
Maybe things can change.
也许事情会有所改变

864
00:58:28,922 --> 00:58:31,016
What Iaw's gonna say you gotta be nice to your maid?
谁跟你说要对女仆好的？

865
00:58:31,174 --> 00:58:32,721
You don't have to do this now, Minny.
你不必这个样，Minny

866
00:58:32,884 --> 00:58:34,511
You damn right I don't!
太对了我不该这样

867
00:58:35,345 --> 00:58:37,393
You two give me the heart palpitations.
你俩真让我心寒

868
00:58:39,933 --> 00:58:41,185

869
00:58:41,893 --> 00:58:42,985
And that's a good mood.
她这算心情好的了

870
00:58:43,145 --> 00:58:44,488

871
00:58:44,646 --> 00:58:47,149

872
00:58:55,115 --> 00:58:57,538
All right. I'm gonna do it.
好的. 我来吧

873
00:58:57,701 --> 00:59:01,672
But I need to make sure she understands this ain't no game we playing here.
但是我要确保她明白我们不是在玩游戏

874
00:59:03,707 --> 00:59:06,335
Slide your chair out from under that table. Face me.
把椅子挪出来，面对我

875
00:59:09,129 --> 00:59:12,884
I need to see you square on at all times.
我要确保你一直端端正正的面对我

876
00:59:22,601 --> 00:59:24,194
I gotta come up with your questions, too?
你不是要问我问题吗？

877
00:59:24,352 --> 00:59:25,444
Oh.
哦

878
00:59:26,813 --> 00:59:31,034
Uh, let's begin with where you were born.
从你在哪出生开始吧

879
00:59:31,193 --> 00:59:34,948
Belzoni, Mississippi, on my great-auntie's sofa.
Belzoni，密西西比，在我曾伯母的沙发上

880
00:59:35,113 --> 00:59:36,239
Next.
下一个

881
00:59:36,406 --> 00:59:38,750
- I put the green beans in first. - OK.
-我先放进绿豆 -好的

882
00:59:38,909 --> 00:59:42,038
Then I get on the pork chops so I can get started on that cornbread.
然后把猪肉切好 接着开始弄玉米面包

883
00:59:42,204 --> 00:59:45,708
Once Minny got to talking about food, she liked to never stop.
一旦Minny谈起食物，她就滔滔不绝

884
00:59:47,459 --> 00:59:51,180
And when she got to talking about the white ladies, it took all night.
而当她谈起白人小姐，这晚就没完了

885
00:59:51,338 --> 00:59:55,844
Then she say, "Oh, Minny, I'm gonna give you a paid vacation."
然后她说，“哦，Minny，我会给你一个带薪假期”

886
00:59:56,009 --> 00:59:58,558
I ain't never had no paid vacation in my life.
这辈子我从没有过带薪假期

887
00:59:58,720 --> 01:00:01,314
A week later I come back, and they done moved to Mobile.
一周后我回来时，他们已经搬家去了Mobile

888
01:00:01,473 --> 01:00:02,520

889
01:00:02,682 --> 01:00:05,902
Miss Lazy Fingers scared I'd find a new job before she moved.
懒指头小姐害怕我在她搬家前找到新工作

890
01:00:06,061 --> 01:00:08,109
Ain't that right, Aibileen?
对吧，Aibileen？

891
01:00:13,819 --> 01:00:15,446
We gots to get some more maids.
我们得再去找些女仆

892
01:00:16,488 --> 01:00:18,957
It hard. You go try and see.
很难.你尽管去试试

893
01:00:21,243 --> 01:00:22,745
OK, I will.
好，我会去的

894
01:00:29,209 --> 01:00:30,586
We gone and done it now.
我们赶紧了结这事吧

895
01:00:30,752 --> 01:00:32,629

896
01:00:33,171 --> 01:00:38,348
Skeeter! Get down here! Something just arrived from New York for you.
Skeeter！快下来！有东西刚从纽约寄来给你

897
01:00:46,560 --> 01:00:47,561

898
01:00:53,942 --> 01:00:54,943
What is that?
是什么？

899
01:00:55,110 --> 01:00:58,785
The Shinalator. All the way from New York City.
烫发机.从纽约寄来的

900
01:00:59,614 --> 01:01:02,493
I'm a good mother.Come on. Sit down.
我是个好母亲，快，坐下

901
01:01:04,077 --> 01:01:09,299
The whole system cost 11 dollars.Even smells expensive.
整套机器可花了11美元，闻起来都是钱味

902
01:01:10,959 --> 01:01:14,384
You're gonna look beautiful on your date tonight.
今晚约会你一定美极了！

903
01:01:14,546 --> 01:01:16,890
I can feel the hope in your fingers.
你的一触一碰让我芙蓉初发

904
01:01:19,885 --> 01:01:21,887
Holy shit.
我去

905
01:01:22,053 --> 01:01:24,647
- You shrunk five inches. - Oh, my God.
-你稍矮了5英寸 -哦，我的天

906
01:01:24,806 --> 01:01:26,854
You'll be able to wear heels tonight.
今晚你得穿上高跟鞋

907
01:01:27,684 --> 01:01:31,029
You're not leaving the house in those awful Mexican man shoes.
穿着那些墨西哥鞋可不准你离开

908
01:01:31,188 --> 01:01:32,280
Can I take the Cadillac?
我能开车去吗？

909
01:01:32,439 --> 01:01:34,862
We promised the Cadillac to Carlton and Rebecca tonight,
我们答应今晚把车借给Carlton和Rebecca

910
01:01:35,025 --> 01:01:38,154
so William's cousin will just have to come pick you up himself.
这样William的表兄就得亲自上门接你

911
01:01:38,320 --> 01:01:40,914
- I'll take the truck. - it's hooked up to the motor grader.
-那我开卡车 -它和平地机连在一起

912
01:01:41,072 --> 01:01:42,073
I'll drive slow.
我会慢慢开

913
01:01:42,240 --> 01:01:44,993
Skeeter! Skeeter!

914
01:01:45,160 --> 01:01:50,007
Now remember, no gentleman wants to spend the evening with a sourpuss.
记住，没有人想和讨厌鬼呆一晚上

915
01:01:50,165 --> 01:01:53,419
Don't mope! Smile!
别没精打采！要微笑！

916
01:01:53,585 --> 01:01:58,933
And for heaven's sakes, don't sit like some squaw Indian! Cross your ankles!
还有坐姿别大咧咧的，要叉腿！

917
01:02:00,133 --> 01:02:01,601
I love you!
爱你！

918
01:02:11,061 --> 01:02:12,654
Stuart, she'll be here any minute.
Stuart，她马上就到

919
01:02:14,439 --> 01:02:15,486
-Hi
-嗨

920
01:02:17,817 --> 01:02:19,160
Skeeter.

921
01:02:21,488 --> 01:02:25,538
Boys, we'll be right back. Y'all talk about quarterbacks or something.
我们马上回来.你们先聊聊四分卫什么的

922
01:02:25,700 --> 01:02:27,498
Yule Mae, get Miss Skeeter a Coca-Cola.
Yule Mae，给Skeeter小姐拿个可乐

923
01:02:27,661 --> 01:02:28,833
Yes, ma'am.
是的，夫人

924
01:02:30,413 --> 01:02:34,589

925
01:02:40,423 --> 01:02:41,424

926
01:02:43,051 --> 01:02:44,052
Want a drink?
喝一杯？

927
01:02:44,219 --> 01:02:46,017
Just water, please.
水就好

928
01:02:47,472 --> 01:02:51,443
Double Old Kentucky, straight with a water back. Make that two backs.
一杯双份波本威士忌不加水，两杯不加水

929
01:02:51,601 --> 01:02:54,480
You sure you don't want to just make it the whole bottle and a straw?
你干脆整瓶打开插吸管喝好了

930
01:02:55,272 --> 01:02:57,946
Honey, there's the lieutenant governor. Let's go say hi.
亲爱的，那是州长助理，我们过去打个招呼

931
01:03:02,404 --> 01:03:04,907
Good to see you, sir. You remember my wife?
见到您真高兴，先生. 还记得我妻子吗？

932
01:03:05,073 --> 01:03:06,290
Hi, how are you? Good to see you.
嗨，你好，见到你很高兴

933
01:03:06,449 --> 01:03:08,122

934
01:03:11,371 --> 01:03:14,671
So, what do you do with your time?
平常你都干些什么？

935
01:03:15,834 --> 01:03:16,881
You work?
你工作吗？

936
01:03:17,669 --> 01:03:19,091
I write.
我写作

937
01:03:20,130 --> 01:03:22,633
But right now I'm working on a domestic maintenance column
现在专职于一个家庭生活专栏

938
01:03:22,799 --> 01:03:23,891
for The Jackson Journal.
为Jackson日报

939
01:03:26,011 --> 01:03:27,183
You mean housekeeping.
你是指家政管理吧

940
01:03:28,346 --> 01:03:31,896
Jesus, I can't think of anything worse than reading a cleaning column,
上帝，还有比读清洁专栏更糟的事吗

941
01:03:32,058 --> 01:03:33,901
except for maybe writing one.
那就是自己动手写

942
01:03:34,060 --> 01:03:35,607
Well, I can.
这我知道

943
01:03:35,770 --> 01:03:39,866
Working with a bunch of greasy, stinky men in the middle of the ocean.
最糟就是在大海上和一群油腻发臭的男人工作

944
01:03:40,025 --> 01:03:43,529
It sounds like a ploy to find a husband, becoming an expert in keeping house.
在成为家政女王的同时找男人看来是个不错的消遣

945
01:03:43,695 --> 01:03:47,325
Well, aren't you a genius? You figured out my whole scheme.
你真聪明，完全被你看穿了

946
01:03:47,490 --> 01:03:50,710
Isn't that what all you girls from Ole Miss major in...
你们这些从Ole Miss毕业的女孩...

947
01:03:50,869 --> 01:03:52,587
...professional husband hunting?
...专业不就是找男人吗？

948
01:03:52,746 --> 01:03:55,670
Who is hungry?
谁饿了？

949
01:03:55,832 --> 01:03:59,427
I'm sorry, but were you dropped on your head as an infant?
抱歉，你婴儿时被摔坏脑子了吧？

950
01:03:59,586 --> 01:04:01,179
Or were you just born stupid?
还是你天生就愚蠢？

951
01:04:01,338 --> 01:04:02,590

952
01:04:12,724 --> 01:04:14,601

953
01:04:19,272 --> 01:04:21,070

954
01:04:23,026 --> 01:04:25,074
So, what can you cook?
你都会烹饪什么？

955
01:04:26,363 --> 01:04:29,663
Oh, um, I can cook cornpone.
哦，我会做玉米饼

956
01:04:30,825 --> 01:04:32,327
Boil potatoes.
炖土豆

957
01:04:33,370 --> 01:04:34,462
I can do grits.
做玉米粉

958
01:04:34,621 --> 01:04:36,669

959
01:04:37,999 --> 01:04:39,046
Well...
这个

960
01:04:39,959 --> 01:04:43,884
...I reckon if there's anything you ought to know about cooking, it's this.
我想烹饪方面你必须知道的一件事就是这个

961
01:04:44,047 --> 01:04:47,142
The most important invention since they put mayonnaise in a jar.
自把蛋黄酱装进罐子后最重要的发明

962
01:04:49,302 --> 01:04:51,270
- You got gum in your hair,
头发里粘了口香糖

963
01:04:51,429 --> 01:04:53,648
you got a squeaky door hinge...
门铰链吱吱响...

964
01:04:53,807 --> 01:04:54,808
Crisco.
Crisco（一个植物油的牌子)

965
01:04:56,559 --> 01:04:58,186
How pretty.
真漂亮

966
01:05:00,105 --> 01:05:02,028
Looks like frosting.
就像雪霜

967
01:05:02,190 --> 01:05:05,069
You got bags under your eyes.
眼睛下有眼袋

968
01:05:05,235 --> 01:05:07,203
Want to soften your husband's scaly feet.
想要放松丈夫的双脚

969
01:05:08,321 --> 01:05:09,948
Mm-hm. Crisco.
嗯哼. Crisco

970
01:05:11,366 --> 01:05:14,415
But it's best for frying chicken.
但最好的用处是炸鸡腿

971
01:05:15,662 --> 01:05:17,335
Frying chicken just...
炸鸡腿...

972
01:05:18,498 --> 01:05:20,592
...tend to make you feel better about life.
...会让你感觉世间如此美妙

973
01:05:24,129 --> 01:05:25,551
At least me, anyway.
至少对我是这样

974
01:05:26,923 --> 01:05:29,597
Mm, I love me some fried chicken.
我爱死炸鸡腿了

975
01:05:31,177 --> 01:05:32,269
Now...
现在...

976
01:05:34,305 --> 01:05:35,306
...shake that.
...摇一摇

977
01:05:35,473 --> 01:05:36,975
Oh.
哦

978
01:05:41,813 --> 01:05:44,657
This is so much fun!
这真有趣！

979
01:05:46,067 --> 01:05:49,537
All right, all right. The chicken already dead, Miss Celia.
好了，小鸡已经死透了，Celia小姐

980
01:05:49,737 --> 01:05:52,411

981
01:05:53,283 --> 01:05:54,660
Yep. He dead.
是的，死绝了

982
01:06:00,748 --> 01:06:02,250

983
01:06:05,837 --> 01:06:07,180
There you are.
你在这呢

984
01:06:08,506 --> 01:06:13,387
I'm starved. Looks so good.
饿死我了，看起来真好吃

985
01:06:13,928 --> 01:06:15,646
We done been over this, Miss Celia.
我们已经说好了，Celia小姐

986
01:06:15,805 --> 01:06:19,685
You supposed to eat in the dining room. That's how it works.
你该在餐厅用餐，事情就该这样

987
01:06:19,851 --> 01:06:21,023
Let me take your plate back.
我帮你把盘子拿过去

988
01:06:21,686 --> 01:06:23,780
I'm fine right here, Minny.
我在这里很好，Minny

989
01:06:35,617 --> 01:06:37,415

990
01:06:43,291 --> 01:06:44,292
What?
什么？

991
01:06:45,752 --> 01:06:47,971
I just want you to know I'm real grateful you're here.
我就想让你知道你能在这我很感激

992
01:06:48,129 --> 01:06:50,882
You gots plenty more to be grateful for than me.
你要感激的事不该是我

993
01:06:52,300 --> 01:06:55,645
And look, now I ain't messing around no more.
看，趁现在事情还没变糟

994
01:06:55,803 --> 01:06:57,100
Now Mr. Johnny gonna catch me here,
如果Johnny先生在这把我抓个正着

995
01:06:57,263 --> 01:07:00,107
and shoot me dead right here on this no-wax floor.
一枪把我射死在这没打蜡的地板上

996
01:07:01,184 --> 01:07:02,231
You gots to tell him.
你得告诉他

997
01:07:02,393 --> 01:07:05,237
Ain't he wondering how the cooking's so good?
他不会好奇食物怎么突然可口起来？

998
01:07:05,396 --> 01:07:07,023
You're right.
你说得对

999
01:07:08,858 --> 01:07:10,860
Maybe we ought to burn the chicken a little.
也许我们该把鸡腿烤焦些

1000
01:07:12,946 --> 01:07:14,619
Minny don't burn chicken.
Minny从不烤焦鸡腿

1001
01:07:17,325 --> 01:07:20,955
I like this Sarah Ross. She testifies without complaining too much.
我喜欢Sarah Ross，她作证却不会抱怨太多

1002
01:07:21,120 --> 01:07:24,750
And that Bertha, she's got chutzpah, I'll give her that.
至于Bertha，她就是一个厚脸皮

1003
01:07:24,916 --> 01:07:26,259
So you liked it?
所以你喜欢这故事？

1004
01:07:26,417 --> 01:07:29,045
Eugenia, Martin Luther King just invited
Eugenia，马丁・路德・金 在八月

1005
01:07:29,212 --> 01:07:32,182
the entire country to march with him in D.C. in August.
刚邀请整个国家和他一起游行

1006
01:07:32,340 --> 01:07:33,683
This many Negroes and whites
这么多黑鬼和白人

1007
01:07:33,841 --> 01:07:36,219
have not worked together since Gone with the Wind.
自从《乱世佳人》以来就没一起工作过

1008
01:07:36,386 --> 01:07:39,139
How many stories have you recorded thus far?
到现在你收录了多少故事？

1009
01:07:39,305 --> 01:07:41,307
The ones you've read.
就你现在读到的这些

1010
01:07:41,474 --> 01:07:43,317
Two domestics, that's all?
两个仆人，这就是全部？

1011
01:07:43,476 --> 01:07:44,728

1012
01:07:45,562 --> 01:07:47,485
I'm real close to getting more interviews.
我马上就会有其他的采访

1013
01:07:47,647 --> 01:07:51,652
Don't send me anything else until you do have more maids.
先别给我发任何东西 直到你找到更多女仆

1014
01:07:51,818 --> 01:07:54,662
Yes, ma'am. How... how many more?
好，那...多少才算多？

1015
01:07:54,821 --> 01:07:57,700
I don't know. At least a dozen.
我不知道，至少一打

1016
01:07:57,865 --> 01:08:01,210
My advice to you is to write it and write it fast
我的建议是你赶紧写，抓紧写

1017
01:08:01,369 --> 01:08:03,713
before this whole civil rights thing blows over.
在这整个民权活动结束以前

1018
01:08:03,871 --> 01:08:05,544
Now good night to you, Miss Phelan.
现在该说晚安了，Phelan小姐

1019
01:08:18,011 --> 01:08:20,059
We need a dozen more.
我们还需要一打女仆

1020
01:08:20,888 --> 01:08:25,143
Me and Aibileen done asked everybody we know. Thirty-one maids.
我和Aibileen问过认识的每个人，31个女仆

1021
01:08:26,060 --> 01:08:28,108
They all too scared. Think we crazy.
她们都吓坏了，认为我们疯了

1022
01:08:29,981 --> 01:08:32,109
If we don't get more, we're not getting published.
如果找不到更多女仆，就没法出版发行

1023
01:08:32,275 --> 01:08:35,245
I gots plenty stories, Miss Skeeter.
我有很多故事，Skeeter小姐

1024
01:08:35,403 --> 01:08:38,998
Just write them down and invent the maid that said it.
记下它们然后捏造一个女仆来复述

1025
01:08:39,157 --> 01:08:41,706
You're already making up names. Just make up the maids, too.
你已经捏造了名字，连女仆一起捏造算了

1026
01:08:41,868 --> 01:08:45,793
We're not gonna do that. That would be wrong.
我们不能那样做，那样是不对的

1027
01:08:45,955 --> 01:08:47,298
Don't give up on this, Miss Skeeter.
别轻言放弃，Skeeter小姐

1028
01:08:47,457 --> 01:08:49,084
It wouldn't be real.
那样就不真实了

1029
01:08:50,627 --> 01:08:52,174
They Killed my son.
他们杀死我儿子

1030
01:08:59,969 --> 01:09:02,222
He fell carrying two-by-fours at the mill.
他在磨坊被车撞倒

1031
01:09:03,806 --> 01:09:05,979
Truck run over him, crushed his lung.
卡车碾过他，压碎他的肺

1032
01:09:06,142 --> 01:09:07,735
Aibileen

1033
01:09:11,064 --> 01:09:13,817
That white foreman threw his body on back of a truck.
白人工头把他的尸体扔上卡车

1034
01:09:14,609 --> 01:09:17,488
Drove to the colored hospital...
开车到黑人医院...

1035
01:09:17,654 --> 01:09:19,622
...dumped him there and honked the horn.
...把他扔在那，然后按了下喇叭

1036
01:09:30,083 --> 01:09:34,304
There was nothing they could do, so I brought my baby home.
医生无能为力，我只好把他带回家

1037
01:09:39,050 --> 01:09:41,303
Laid him down on that sofa right there.
他就躺在那沙发上

1038
01:09:44,931 --> 01:09:46,933
He died right in front of me.
他就死在我身前

1039
01:09:49,519 --> 01:09:53,149
He was just 24 years old, Miss Skeeter. Best part of a person's life.
他刚24岁，Skeeter小姐，正值青春年华

1040
01:09:54,774 --> 01:09:58,369
Anniversary of his death comes...
每年他的忌日之际...

1041
01:09:58,528 --> 01:10:00,906
...every year, and I can't breathe.
...每年，我都无法呼吸

1042
01:10:01,072 --> 01:10:03,291
But to y'all, it's just another day of bridge.
对你们来说，那只是桥牌度日的另一天

1043
01:10:07,745 --> 01:10:09,213
You stop this...
你放弃的话...

1044
01:10:10,498 --> 01:10:14,298
...everything I wrote, he wrote, everything he was is gonna die with him.
...我写的，他写的每一件事都将随他逝去

1045
01:10:24,512 --> 01:10:27,732
I am just honored to be hosting Elizabeth's shower.
我很荣幸能为Elizabeth主持这次送礼会

1046
01:10:27,890 --> 01:10:30,109
Doesn't she look glowing, everybody?
她看起来真是美极了，对吧？

1047
01:10:30,268 --> 01:10:32,737
- Yes, she does!
-是，她光彩照人

1048
01:10:32,895 --> 01:10:35,318
Honey, you hold on to it, to the bitter end.
亲爱的，苦日子等着你，你要坚持住

1049
01:10:35,481 --> 01:10:36,824

1050
01:10:36,983 --> 01:10:39,031
- I'll try. - Well, congratulations.
-我会努力的 -不错，恭喜你

1051
01:10:41,070 --> 01:10:43,164
I'm hungry, Mommy.
我饿了，妈妈

1052
01:10:43,322 --> 01:10:44,494
She's always hungry.
她没完没了的饿

1053
01:10:44,657 --> 01:10:46,580

1054
01:10:47,493 --> 01:10:49,086
You know she can hear you, Elizabeth.
你知道她听得到你，Elizabeth

1055
01:10:49,245 --> 01:10:53,500
I'll cut you a piece of cake, baby. Go on, now.
我去帮你切块蛋糕，来

1056
01:10:57,545 --> 01:11:02,392
Aibileen, are you enjoying your new bathroom over at Elizabeth's?
Aibileen, Elizabeth那的新卫生间你还喜欢吧

1057
01:11:02,550 --> 01:11:06,305
Nice to have your own. isn't it, Aibileen?
拥有自己的卫生间很棒吧，Aibileen？

1058
01:11:10,850 --> 01:11:14,150
Yes, ma'am. And I thank you.
是的，夫人，我感谢你

1059
01:11:14,312 --> 01:11:16,986
Separate, but equal.
单独的，但是平等

1060
01:11:17,690 --> 01:11:20,113
That's what Ross Barnett says, and you can't argue with the governor.
Ross Barnett就这样说，你可不能反驳州长

1061
01:11:20,276 --> 01:11:24,497
Well, certainly not in Mississippi,the birthplace of modern-day government.
当然不能，密西西比可是现代政府的发扬地

1062
01:11:40,838 --> 01:11:44,263
Hey, Miss Skeeter. Can I get you something?
嗨，Skeeter小姐，想吃点什么？

1063
01:11:44,425 --> 01:11:45,426
No, thanks.
不用，谢谢

1064
01:11:46,719 --> 01:11:49,097
Yule Mae, I wanted to talk to you about something.
Yule Mae，我想和你谈点事情

1065
01:11:51,682 --> 01:11:53,855
I already know what you're gonna ask, Miss Skeeter.
我知道你要问什么，Skeeter小姐

1066
01:11:56,479 --> 01:11:58,231
Minny and Aibileen already did.
Minny和Aibileen已经问过了

1067
01:12:03,402 --> 01:12:05,996
I'm trying to get my boys off to college.
我正在想办法送孩子们上大学

1068
01:12:07,865 --> 01:12:10,869
It's worthwhile what y'all are doing, but...
你们的所作所为值得付出，但是...

1069
01:12:11,035 --> 01:12:13,629
...but my boys are worth more.
...但我的孩子们更重要

1070
01:12:14,413 --> 01:12:15,460
I understand.
我明白

1071
01:12:19,335 --> 01:12:22,805
What do you understand, Skeeter?
你明白什么，Skeeter？

1072
01:12:24,924 --> 01:12:29,555
Yule Mae was just saying how excited she is that her boys are going to college.
Yule Mae正说她很兴奋 她就要送孩子去上大学了

1073
01:12:30,388 --> 01:12:33,062
Did you also ask Miss Skeeter if you could borrow money?
你向Skeeter小姐借钱了吧？

1074
01:12:33,891 --> 01:12:35,234
Of course not.
当然没有

1075
01:12:37,395 --> 01:12:39,397
I'm gonna put Billy down for his nap.
我去哄Billy睡觉

