现在总算有件值得骄傲的事了

1793
02:11:55,866 --> 02:11:57,868
I don't mean to rub salt in your wound,
我不是要在你伤口上撒盐

1794
02:11:58,035 --> 02:12:00,504
but you ain't got a good life here in Jackson.
但在Jackson这里你的生活真不怎样

1795
02:12:00,663 --> 02:12:02,131
Plus, your mama's getting better.
况且，你妈妈身体也见好转

1796
02:12:02,289 --> 02:12:05,668
You ain't got nothing left here but enemies in the Junior League.
在这里除了社团里的敌人 你什么都没有了

1797
02:12:05,835 --> 02:12:07,758
You done burned every bridge there is.
桥牌聚会被你彻底毁了

1798
02:12:07,920 --> 02:12:10,389
And you ain't never gonna get another man in this town.
而且在镇里你也找不到任何男人

1799
02:12:10,548 --> 02:12:12,767
- Everybody know that.
这个大家都知道

1800
02:12:12,925 --> 02:12:16,350
So don't walk your white butt to New York, run it!
所以还不快去纽约，赶紧滴！

1801
02:12:18,347 --> 02:12:22,022
Looky here, Miss Skeeter. I'm gonna take care of Aibileen.
看，Skeeter小姐，我会照顾Aibileen

1802
02:12:24,186 --> 02:12:25,984
And she's gonna take care of me.
她也会照顾我

1803
02:12:37,741 --> 02:12:40,210
Go find your life, Miss Skeeter.
去闯你自己的人生吧，Skeeter小姐

1804
02:12:53,799 --> 02:12:56,177
Aibileen, can you come in here, please?
Aibileen，你过来下，好吗？

1805
02:13:02,308 --> 02:13:03,355
Good morning.
早上好

1806
02:13:04,101 --> 02:13:08,982
Aibileen, the silver I lent Elizabeth last week.
Aibileen，我上礼拜借给Elizabeth的银器

1807
02:13:09,148 --> 02:13:11,242
It not polished good?
擦的不够亮吗？

1808
02:13:11,400 --> 02:13:14,654
Humidity been fighting me on polishing day.
那天湿气很大 很不好擦

1809
02:13:14,820 --> 02:13:19,496
When you returned it, three pieces were missing from the felt wrapper.
你还回来的时候少了三件

1810
02:13:20,826 --> 02:13:24,080
- A fork and two spoons.
一把叉子和两个汤匙

1811
02:13:24,246 --> 02:13:27,796
Let me... Let me go check in the kitchen. Maybe I left some behind.
我...再去厨房找找，也许落在什么地方了

1812
02:13:27,958 --> 02:13:31,007
You know as well as I do that silver's not in the kitchen.
你我心里都明白银器不在厨房

1813
02:13:33,339 --> 02:13:35,592
You check in Mae Mobley's bed?
Mae Mobley的床上你看过没？

1814
02:13:36,717 --> 02:13:38,811
Since the Lil Man was born, she been putting things...
自从Lil Man出生，她一直把东西...

1815
02:13:38,969 --> 02:13:40,721
Do you hear her, Elizabeth?
你听到没，Elizabeth?

1816
02:13:41,764 --> 02:13:43,562
She's trying to blame it on a toddler.
她想把责任推给小孩子

1817
02:13:45,726 --> 02:13:47,399
I ain't got no silver.
我什么银器都没拿

1818
02:13:47,561 --> 02:13:49,655
She says she doesn't have them.
她说她没拿

1819
02:13:50,147 --> 02:13:54,402
Then it behooves me to inform you that you are fired, Aibileen.
那我不得不通知你 你被解雇了，Aibileen

1820
02:13:55,528 --> 02:13:57,701
And I'll be calling the police.
然后我会报警

1821
02:13:59,615 --> 02:14:02,414
Aibee, my throat hurts.
Aibee，我的嗓子疼

1822
02:14:04,578 --> 02:14:07,297
I'll go get some syrup, Miss Leefolt.
我去拿些糖浆，Leefolt小姐

1823
02:14:07,998 --> 02:14:10,501
Elizabeth can take care of her own children.
Elizabeth自会照顾她的孩子

1824
02:14:13,921 --> 02:14:16,765
- I'll go get the cough syrup. - Come here, Lil Man.
-我去拿咳嗽糖浆 -来，Lil Man

1825
02:14:16,924 --> 02:14:18,346
I'm OK.
我能行

1826
02:14:28,727 --> 02:14:30,775
I didn't steal no silver.
我什么银器也没偷

1827
02:14:30,938 --> 02:14:34,659
Maybe I can't send you to jail for what you wrote,
也许我不能因为你写的东西送你进监狱

1828
02:14:34,817 --> 02:14:36,694
but I can send you for being a thief.
但你做贼的话 我就能

1829
02:14:36,860 --> 02:14:39,283
I know something about you. Don't you forget that.
我知道你的事，你别忘了

1830
02:14:39,989 --> 02:14:43,118
From what Yule Mae says, there's a lot of time to write letters in jail.
从Yule Mae那我知道监狱里有不少时间来写信

1831
02:14:43,284 --> 02:14:46,959
Plenty of time to write the truth about you. And the paper is free.
足够多的时间写下你那些事，纸还是免费的

1832
02:14:47,121 --> 02:14:49,795
- Nobody will believe what you wrote! - I don't know!
-没人会相信你写的东西 -我不知道

1833
02:14:50,332 --> 02:14:53,632
I been told I'm a pretty good writer. Already sold a lot of books.
大家都说我是个好作者，书已经卖了很多

1834
02:14:58,382 --> 02:15:00,555
Call the police, Elizabeth.
去报警，Elizabeth

1835
02:15:01,302 --> 02:15:04,021
All you do is scare and lie to try to get what you want.
为了得到你想要的 你只会威胁和撒谎

1836
02:15:04,179 --> 02:15:05,180
Aibileen, stop!
Aibileen，停！

1837
02:15:05,347 --> 02:15:07,395
You a godless woman.
你个目无上帝的女人

1838
02:15:09,435 --> 02:15:11,529
Ain't you tired, Miss Hilly?
你不累吗，Hily小姐？

1839
02:15:14,189 --> 02:15:15,532
Ain't you tired?
不累吗？

1840
02:15:28,954 --> 02:15:31,377
Aibileen, you have to go now.
Aibileen，你得走了

1841
02:15:46,013 --> 02:15:48,436
Don't go, Aibee.
别走，Aibee

1842
02:15:49,642 --> 02:15:51,986
Baby, you need to get back to bed.
宝贝，你快回床上去

1843
02:15:52,519 --> 02:15:56,569
- Please don't leave. -I gots to, baby. I am so sorry.
-请不要走 -我必须走，宝贝，抱歉

1844
02:15:56,732 --> 02:15:59,485
Are you going to take care of another little girl?
你是要去照顾其他女孩子吗？

1845
02:15:59,652 --> 02:16:01,620
No, that's not the reason.
不，不是因为那个

1846
02:16:01,779 --> 02:16:05,329
I don't want to leave you, but it's time for me to retire.
我不想离开你，但我该退休了

1847
02:16:05,491 --> 02:16:07,744
- You're my last little girl. - No!
-你是我最后一个女孩 -不要

1848
02:16:07,910 --> 02:16:09,912
Baby. Baby.
宝贝

1849
02:16:10,913 --> 02:16:13,416
I need you to remember everything I told you, OK?
我要你记住我跟你说过的话，好吗？

1850
02:16:13,582 --> 02:16:15,710
- OK. - You remember what I told you?
-好 -你还记得我跟你说的吗？

1851
02:16:15,876 --> 02:16:21,303
You is kind. You is smart.
你很善良，你很聪明

1852
02:16:21,465 --> 02:16:23,138
You is important.
你很重要

1853
02:16:23,300 --> 02:16:25,177
That's right, Baby Girl.
对，宝贝

1854
02:16:30,391 --> 02:16:31,859
Don't go, Aibee.
别走，Aibee

1855
02:16:32,017 --> 02:16:33,234
I gots to, baby.
我得走了，宝贝

1856
02:16:35,896 --> 02:16:37,819
You give my sweet girl a chance.
你记得给我的女孩一个机会

1857
02:16:54,123 --> 02:16:56,376
Mae Mobley was my last baby.
Mae Mobley是我照顾的最后一个孩子

1858
02:16:58,836 --> 02:17:01,715
In just ten minutes, the only life l knew was done.
不到十分钟里，我以前熟知的生活彻底远去

1859
02:17:01,880 --> 02:17:04,599
Aibee!

1860
02:17:07,970 --> 02:17:10,064
God says we need to love our enemies.
上帝说我们要爱我们的敌人

1861
02:17:10,222 --> 02:17:11,565
No!
不！

1862
02:17:13,475 --> 02:17:14,818
It hard to do.
这很难做到

1863
02:17:21,066 --> 02:17:23,194
But it can start by telling the truth.
但可以从说真话做起

1864
02:17:28,365 --> 02:17:31,960
No one had ever asked me what it felt like to be me.
没人问过我做我自己是什么感觉

1865
02:17:35,330 --> 02:17:37,378
Once I told the truth about that...
要我来说的话...

1866
02:17:39,376 --> 02:17:41,049
...I felt free.
...我感觉自由

1867
02:17:49,470 --> 02:17:52,565
And I got to thinking about all the people l know.
我开始考虑认识的每个人

1868
02:17:54,600 --> 02:17:56,602
And the things I seen and done.
我所见过经历过的

1869
02:18:02,357 --> 02:18:06,703
My boy, Treelore, always said we going to have a writer in the family one day.
我的孩子 Treelore总说 我们家迟早要出个作家

1870
02:18:10,032 --> 02:18:12,160
I guess it's gonna be me.
我想那人是我

